GOOOALLLL!!! City double their lead and it's 2-0!!!! Mahrez, who won the penalty, sends Mignolet the wrong way to dispatch the spot-kick and likely send City into half-time with a two-goal cushion!
Moumi Ngamaleu goes into the book for a poor challenge on Zappacosta. The Atalanta wing-back is still down and receiving treatment.
De Paul catches Ronaldo with a late challenge and goes into the book.
Vinicius talks himself into the book after appealing to the referee about Nacho's card.

LILLE LEVEL! David dispatches the spot-kick to the left side of the goal, and despite Bounou guessing the right way, Sevilla's goalkeeper can do nothing to keep the ball out of the net. It is now 1-1!
Nacho goes into the book for a late lunge on Hakimi. He has to be careful now.
Nielsen joins Brorsson in the book, after his hands-on challenge on Morata in the centre of the area.
Vida is shown a yellow card for that handball.
Inter right-back Darmian is booked for a poor challenge.
It's just a simple square pass from Coman into Sane after he spotted his team-mate in acres of space.

SANE SCORES! The German is a long way out when he's teed up by Coman, but the space just opens up ahead of him. He takes a touch before firing it at the near top corner. Ter Stegen has a good view of it and should do better as he gets across to it. It takes a touch off his arm before hitting the back of the net. 2-0 Bayern!
Hudson-Odoi comes on to replace Werner. He'll play on the left of Chelsea's front three.
Yaremchuk is the second Benfica player to be booked after his poor challenge on Zabarnyi.
SARABIA SLOTS IT IN! 3-1! Sarabia steps up confidently and sends Destanoglu the wrong way, before rolling it into the bottom right corner.
Sterling gets involved with an assist, but the way City are playing, it might not be long before he gets himself on the scoresheet.

GOAAAALLL - SPORTING 0-4 MAN CITY. Bernardo gets his second of the night, but this one takes a wicked deflection on its way past Adan. Cancelo's crossfield pass picked out Sterling, who cut the ball back for Bernardo. The City midfielder aimed his shot towards the near post, but the deflection helped beat the Sporting keeper, and Guardiola's side are cruising.
Tsygankov slams into Joao Mario with an awkward challenge and is shown a yellow card.
Santos touches the ball in and Schuurs is very late as he slides in. He takes the forward's legs out from under him and is shown a yellow card.
For his vocal disapproval of the red card for Welinton, his Besiktas colleague Souza is booked.

MILAN LEAD! Liverpool look completely shocked after dominating the game for 40 minutes, they're not 2-1 down! Leao's driving run cuts open Liverpool's defence and he slides it through to Rebic and he picks out Hernandez. His shot is blocked by Alexander-Arnold on the line and Diaz follows in to tap it in.
N'Soki, who conceded the penalty, catches De Bruyne late and is booked. Not the best few minutes for the Brugge defender.
Verissimo is also booked for the foul inside the penalty area, a clear handball to block the shot by Goretzka.
Xeka is shown a yellow card after clumsily colliding with Kristensen.
Otamendi wipes out Kimmich with a strong challenge and goes into the book.
Aebischer is yellow carded by the referee, having impeded a run forward by Capoue.
Ajax midfielder Berghuis is shown the second yellow card of the match after a sloppy challenge in midfield.
Addo is booked for preventing Valverde from reaching his flick over the Sheriff midfielder's head. Sheriff see out Madrid's free-kick and that's all for now.
Two changes for Sporting at the break - the first sees Reis replace Vinagre.
Montero joins his centre-back partner in being booked for a foul on Haaland. The free-kick is in a dangerous position just outside the box and to the right of goal.

GOAL! Liverpool double their lead just before the break! It's a brilliant cross into the box from the right wing by Milner, catching the Porto defence and keeper out, with Costa coming out to block the cross, but he completely misses the ball! It then falls to Mane at the far post, who had a simple tap-in from just a few yards out. Liverpool go 2-0 up.
Azpilicueta gets caught wrong side of Azmoun and throws out an arm to try and shield him from the ball. He catches him in the face and is shown the first yellow card of the game.
JUVE DOUBLE UP! Dybala scuffs his penalty low underneath Diawara, but gets enough purchase to secure a second Juventus goal of the first half. Now it's Malmo 0-2 Juventus!
Milner had a couple of teammates to aim for in the penalty area and he whipped a fantastic cross into the box and when it fell to Mane, he simply couldn't miss.
Shkurin's not led the line with much vigour in the first half, and Vitinho comes on to replace him at half-time.

INCREDIBLE! Having earned a penalty just a few minutes previously, Morata then nets a third Juventus goal! Dybala's attempts at latching onto a long ball cause confusion in the Malmo defence and the former Real Madrid man pokes his long leg out to steer the ball past Diawara. Remarkably, Juventus lead 3-0 at the break!
De Pena is also withdrawn for Dynamo, replaced by Denys Harmash.
Martinez goes into the book for dissent just before the break.
Rose has had a half-time rethink, and Schulz has been replaced by Can for Dortmund.
Laimer is replaced by Haidara.
Marsch does indeed choose to make changes, the first being Mukiele off for Gvardiol.
Alaba is forced off for the visitors at the break and is replaced by Nacho.
Hernandez's night is done for Bayern, as on comes Bouna Sarr in his place.
Foden also comes off, and is replaced by fellow academy graduate James McAtee.
Sanusi - who was on a yellow card - is replaced by Wendell at left-back.
There's a change for Barcelona at the break. Dest, who struggled to make an impact in the first half, is replaced by Gonzalez.
The visitors have withdrawn Taarabt at the interval, and former Torino midfielder Meite is on in hs place.
Zappacosta is forced off with that injury and is replaced at half-time by Pezzella, who goes to left wing-back, with Maehle switching to the right.
Tuchel has opted to shuffle his pack during the interval, and Kovacic has been replaced by Mount for the second 45.
Hermoso is also making way, with Lodi on for him.
Simeone is making a double change at the start of the second half. De Paul is the first to come on, replacing Carrasco.
Boban Nikolov replaces Dimitris Kolovos in Sheriff's first change of the game.
Tete replaces Heorhii Sudakov in Shakhtar Donetsk's first change of the game.
Mykhailo Mudryk replaces Fernando in Shakhtar Donetsk's second change of the game.
Inter make a half-time substitution. Dumfries goes off after a lacklustre first half. Dimarco replaces him.
The Sheriff captain, Castaneda Velez, is replaced by Radeljic as the visitors switch to a back three for the second half to match up Inter.
There's been a double change for the hosts too, with Lucas Ocampos on for Suso.
Porto have made a change ahead of the second half, with Martinez coming off and he has been replaced by former Liverpool man Grujic.
City make two half-times substitutions, with the first seeing Silva withdrawn for Riyad Mahrez.
Inzaghi has chosen to replace De Vrij with D'Ambrosio in a change to his back three. It remains to be seen whether that will entail a change of shape.
Chilwell replaces Alonso at the break for the Blues.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!! CHIESA SCORES 11 SECONDS AFTER THE RESTART!!!! 1-0 JUVE!!!! The Bianconeri enjoy the perfect start to the second half as Chiesa hammers home a close-range finish. Juve catch Chelsea asleep at the back as Bernardeschi releases Chiesa in the left-inside channel. The Italian takes on the strike first time on his left foot and he fires his effort into the top-left corner giving Mendy no chance.
Jota is withdrawn at the break for the visitors and is replaced by Firmino.
There's a change for Liverpool at the break. Mane, who is on a yellow card, is taken off, with Firmino on in his place.
Gimenez enters the action in place of Kondogbia in the heart of the Atletico defence.
Keita is withdrawn after struggling defensively in the first half. Fabinho replaces the midfielder.
Juventus are making a change at the break and it's Bonucci that's coming on to replace Alex Sandro.
Calabria, who may have picked up a knock on the stroke of half-time, makes way for Kalulu at the break.
Rose makes a half-time change with his side leading, replacing Brandt with Witsel in midfield.
Klaassen replaces Alvarez in the Ajax midfield at the break. Ten Hag is taking no chances with the midfielder already on a yellow card.
Substitution Merih Demiral Berat Djimsiti
Substitution Matteo Pessina Ruslan Malinovskyi
Herrera clips Pogba's heels before tugging the Frenchman's shirt when he gets away from him. He's shown the first yellow card of the game.
Klostermann's indiscretion earns him a yellow card. Mahrez will be the City player to take the penalty.
Wendell, who picked up a knock towards the end of the first half, doesn't come back out and is replaced by Sanusi.
Nunez is booked for a reckless challenge on Martinez, and he will need to calm down before he is sent to the stands!
Solet also makes way for Salzburg, with Piatkowski getting the chance to impress off the bench.
Gnabry is given an early night, with Sarr the one to replace him.
Salzburg boss Matthias Jaissle turns to his bench at the break as Seiwald is replaced by Sucic.
Yalcin throws on attacker Teixeira for centre-back Montero as he attempts to reduce the hosts' three-goal lead.
PSG have made a double substitution ahead of the second half, with Wijnaldum one of those coming off and he has been replaced by Draxler.
Cabral also makes way, with Sarabia coming on in his place.
Timber is the second player to be carded after a miss-timed challenge near the halfway line.
Leipzig have made a change ahead of the second half, with Orban the man coming off and he has been replaced by Haidara.
Demiral, who looked like he was struggling with a muscle injury during the first time, hasn't come back out after the break, so Lovato replaces him.
Tete is withdrawn at the break by the visitors and is replaced by Marlos.
One change at the break for Juventus as Morata replaces Dybala!
Dodi Lukebakio replaces Yannick Gerhardt in Wolfsburg's first change of the game.
The other change sees Paredes head off and he has been replaced by Danilo.
Bernardeschi releases the run of Chiesa with an incisive pass before the forward does the rest with a great finish.
Jordan has meanwhile made way for Thomas Delaney for Sevilla.
Lopetegui blinks first and sends Rekik on for Acuna.
There's a change at the break for Ajax. Blind isn't coming back out for the second half, with Tagliafico on for him.
Ziyech is also on for Kante, with Chelsea seemingly playing a 4-3-3 now.
Chelsea are making a half-time switch here, with Kovacic entering the fray to replace Christensen, as the Blues change system.
Benfica will make that change now. Gilberto replaces Lazaro at right wing-back.
Buyalskyi goes into the book for a heavy challenge on Gaviria.
Gavi gets a booking early into this second half for a foul on Karavaev.
Coutinho replaces Mingueza on the field as Koeman looks to up the ante in the second half. Dest will drop into right-back.

GOAL! SHERIFF 0-2 REAL MADRID! Kroos doubles Madrid's lead with a fantastic strike! The German receives Rodrygo's pass and smashes the ball towards goal from outside the box. It rebounds off the crossbar and straight down into the net. It just crosses the line.
Lovren also makes way with Erokhin taking his place. This change signals Zenit's intent as a defender is replaced by an attacker.
Zenit attempt to shake things up with a substitution at half-time: Mostovoy comes on for Claudinho in attack.
And for Leipzig, it's Simakan that's replacing Klostermann.
There's a change for both sides at the start of the second half. For City, Sterling is on for Foden.
The second half is only a few seconds old and already, Karavaev has been shown a yellow for a rash challenge on Chiesa. It's eager - too eager - and he pays the price for it.
Young Boys also make a change as they attempt to chase the game. The American striker Siebatcheu replaces Sierro.
De Jong is withdrawn after a difficult first half and is replaced by Fati.
Liverpool make a change at the break with Luis Diaz replacing Jota.
Dulanto picks up a yellow card early in the half for tripping Valverde down Madrid's right.
PENALTY SAVED! Vlachodimos waits as long as he can before he has to pick a side and he reads the effort from Lewandowski superbly, making an excellent save to deny the striker. It remains 2-1.
Dost is also hauled off at half-time, with Rits his replacement.
Clement turns to his bench for a double change, with N'Soki replaced by Rostagnol.
Nkunku's night gets better as he picks up an assist to add to his earlier goal after teeing up Forsberg.

GOAAALLLL - CLUB BRUGGE 0-4 RB LEIPZIG - FORSBERG TAKE A BOW. The Leipzig midfielder now has two for the night, and that's the pick of the goals so far. He was allowed to cut inside from the left wing, and once he made his way towards the box, the home side were in trouble. He managed to outfox Mignolet in goal before firing into the near post, and the former Liverpool stopper had no chance.
Meunier has been withdrawn during the interval, to be replaced by Reinier for the second half.

LEWANDOWSKI MISSES! The striker doesn't take a very good run up to the penalty and waits for the keeper to make a move, before firing the ball towards the bottom left corner of the net. However, he doesn't get enough pace on it and Vlachodimos reacts quickly and makes the save. Great stop by the keeper, but's it's a really poor penalty by Lewandowski.
Fassnacht is booked for his mistimed challenge. It's not that dissimilar from the one that saw Wan-Bissaka sent off.
Benfica have made a half-time change, as Goncalves makes way for Yaremchuk, who will join Nunez up front.
United make a half-time change as they switch to a back three. Van de Beek is replaced by Varane.
event_player: [' R. Varane ', ' D. van de Beek ']

comment: Karaman barely had a kick in the opening half, and is now replaced by Rosier, as Sergen Yalcin seeks to reshape his undermanned defence.
Malmo make two changes at the break. Diawara takes Dahlin's place as goalkeeper first.
Dynamo have made a double substitution ahead of the second half, with Tymchyk one of those to come off and he has been replaced by Kedziora.
Rose makes an interesting change at half-time, replacing left-back Schulz with a midfielder in Can.
Antonio, who just came on, is booked for a tough challenge on Casemiro.
Marlos also comes on for Tete.
Yilmaz makes way for Tore.
Stepanenko, who was an injury doubt before kick-off, is replaced by Antonio at half-time.
Next to come off is Birmancevic who's made little impact on the game. Abubakari replaces him up front.
Ucan is replaced by Ozyakup.
Shaparenko is the other man to come off and he has been replaced by Shepelev.
Fernandes timed his run perfectly and stayed the right side of Palomino to just flick the ball back into Ronaldo's path.
Haller is on for Daramy at the break. The French striker has scored seven goals so far in this season's competition.
Antonio is on for Solomon at the break.

GOAAALLL! 3-1 TO REAL MADRID, AND IT'S ANOTHER CHAMPIONS LEAGUE HAT-TRICK FOR BENZEMA! Oh my word, what are Chelsea playing at here? It's a calamitous start to the second half for the hosts, as Mendy's terrible pass towards Rudiger allows Benzema to roll into an empty net!
There's a change for Atalanta at the break. Djimsiti comes on and slots into the back three, with De Roon moving further forward. Pasalic is the player making way.
Rodrygo claims the assist but take nothing away from Kroos' strike. That was as pure as they come. Sheriff restart play but the half-time whistle blows shortly after.

RONALDO EQUALISES! It's brilliant from United as they pass it in between Atalanta on the edge of the box. Ronaldo touches it onto Greenwood, who slides it into Fernandes, and his flick opens up the space for Ronaldo in the middle. He takes a touch before firing it past Musso, who couldn't get near it. 1-1!
Brooks is booked after hauling Yilmaz down near the touchline.
Teixeira is booked after remonstrating with the Sporting players, following a cynical foul by Nunes.
DORTMUND DOUBLE UP! After a delay, Reus step up to slot his spot kick home coolly, as his penalty nestles in the bottom-left corner of the net. Die Schwarzgelben lead 2-0!
Inzaghi is clearly unhappy with his team's first-half display as Darmian is replaced by Dumfries at the break.
Sucic breaks forward for Salzburg with pace, but is fouled by Mbabu as he looks to pick a pass. Mbabu is booked as a result.
GOAL! MANCHESTER CITY 3-1 RB LEIPZIG! Mahrez steps up and sweeps the penalty into the top right corner with his left foot. Gulacsi is nowhere near it.
Estupinan pulls back Salah off the ball and goes into the book. That was as cynical as it gets.
Robertson picks up a booking early in the second half, as he brings down Dumfries in his own half.
Chelsea countered with pace and purpose there and Hudson-Odoi was at the heart of it. It's surely job done for the Londoners.
Gueye scythes Silva down late, and is not only booked, but concedes in-range for Nkunku to have an effort at goal, from the free-kick.

GOAL! CHELSEA 3-0 MALMO! Chelsea give Diawara a torrid welcome in the torrential rain! Malmo get caught upfield and the hosts counter through Hudson-Odoi. The winger slips in Havertz who dinks the ball over the keeper into the far bottom corner.

Bellingham made another clever run off the ball to get into space in the box, allowing Guerreiro's throw to take several men out of the game. The midfielder then showed quick feet to beat his man and awareness to slide the ball into Haaland for an easy finish.
GOAL!!! IT'S 2-0 TO DORTMUND!!! Bellingham is found in the box from a throw-in on the left and dances past one challenge before squaring to Haaland, who tucks the ball away from six yards out!
Origi just scoops the ball over the top of Tomori to pick out Salah with the return ball and set up the goal.
And it's 1-0 to Wolfsburg! It's Steffen who converts after Lukebakio's cross causes havoc in the defence, allowing the Swiss winger to prod it in after the ball fell to him.

SALAH EQUALISES! And just like that, Liverpool are back level! Salah plays a one-two with Origi to just open up a pocket of space as he pulls off the back of the defender. He lifts his shot over the stranded Maignan and into the bottom corner. After a quick VAR check, the goal stands. 2-2!
Mir is booked for a foul on Steffen as the Swiss winger chested the ball past him.

CHELSEA EQUALISE! After a deliberate Chelsea build-up, Jorginho finds a yard of space around 20 yards from goal and prods through a beautifully weighted pass to pick out Pulisic in the box. The American winger stays cool to cut inside and steer the ball home at the far post; leaving Jardim with no chance. Lille 1-1 Chelsea, and the visitors are now 3-1 ahead on aggregate!
Using his characteristic blend of vision and precision, Jorginho slots through a perfect pass to split the Lille defence and tee up Pulisic to strike.
The referee eventually shows the yellow card to Pique for his initial foul on Yaremchuk.
Grujic catches Tonali late and the Italian midfielder rolls around on the floor. Giroud and the hosts' players protest but the referee has already waved the yellow card at the Liverpool loanee.
Pique tugs Yaremchuk's shirt and isn't dealt with firmly enough in Joao Mario's book. The midfielder winds up in the book himself for questioning the referee's judgment.
Silva claims the assist after his low cross picked out Nunez at the back post, but Konate completely missed his clearance to gift Benfica a route back into this clash!
Adams sees yellow for catching Grealish from behind. City must love having Grealish. The man is a foul magnet.

GOAAAALLL! WE HAVE A GAME IN LISBON! Konate, who has been brilliant all game, is at fault as the Eagles claw a goal back! The Liverpool defender completely misses Silva's low cross, and Nunez is there to finish neatly past Allison! 2-1!
Ramos goes into the referee's book after pulling Timber to the ground.
Rakitskiy cuts back on his right foot after gathering Malcom's cross and he lifts a delivery of his own into the middle to allow Kuzyaev to head home.
Vitao is back on his feet, but he received a yellow card, with the referee claiming he brought down Dzeko intentionally.
A late challenge by Sanchez, with his boot raised, catches Thiago on the leg. That will be a booking for the Inter forward.
Colak picks up the first yellow card of the game after a late challenge off the ball.
Alvarez is shown a yellow card after a strong challenge on Paulinho.

GOAL! SANE MAKES IT 3-1! Once again it's a superb ball from Kimmich to pick out Davies in behind the Benfica defence and the left-back heads the ball back to Sane, who is unmarked in the box and Sane volleys it into the bottom right corner of the net. Great finish by Sane and he gets Bayern off to the perfect start in the second half!

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!! KUZYAEV HEADS HOME ZENIT'S SECOND!!!!! 2-0!!!!! The Russian side double their advantage courtesy of a precise header from Kuzyaev. Malcom sends a dangerous cross into the box from the left flank that evades all the white shirts in the penalty area. Rakitskiy gathers and cuts back on to his right foot to float a cross towards the six-yard box. Kuzyaev rises and directs his header away from Dahlin into the top-left corner.
The assist goes to Davies, but what a ball it is from Kimmich to find Davies down the left! The full-back headed it back towards Sane, who produced an excellent finish to beat Vlachodimos.
Martins is booked for that tackle on Fernandes.
Mbabu is yellow carded after a heavy challenge on Ocampos.
Lenglet also goes in the book after dragging down Tsygankov.

GOOOOOALLLLL!!!! PSG LEAD!!! Messi and Herrera play a lovely one-two on the edge of the box, and Messi's cross is deflected right into the path of Mbappe. He sets himself, and then fires a low shot straight through Ederson's legs and PSG lead 1-0!
Larin also goes into the book for arguing with the referee.
Souza clatters into Paulinho in the middle and then disagrees with the referee's decision to give a free-kick. Unsurprisingly, the away side's midfielder goes into the book.

GOAAALLL - SALZBURG 1-0 SEVILLA - Lift-off for Salzburg, who move one step closer to qualification as they take the lead on home soil. Matthias Jaissle's outfit carved through the Sevilla defence, with Adeyemi collecting possession on the edge of the box. After a free-flowing move, his cross picked out Okafor, who opened up his body before side-footing his shot past Bounou.
Mendes does come off, and on comes Kehrer to slot in at left-back.
Dahlin is shown a yellow card for the foul that conceded the penalty. The goalkeeper will be relieved not to have been sent off.
As we said in the first half, Adeyemi has looked dangerous when on the ball, and he proves his worth to the Salzburg team by creating the opening goal for Okafor.
The first yellow card of the game is shown to Upamecano for his foul on Yaremchuk and this booking means that he will miss Bayern's next Champions League game against Dynamo Kiev.
Shaw takes a heavy first touch and ends up stepping on Vrsaljko's foot in his attempts to win it back. It's a poor challenge, and he's shown a yellow card.
Modric showed his class with a superb throughball to set up Vinicius to beat the keeper.
Joao Felix is booked after catching Taremi with an arm.
Loftus-Cheek replaces Kovacic, who limps off the field for the home side. Tuchel will be hopeful that is not a serious problem.
Sierro catches Capoue on the top of the foot as the pair compete for the ball and the Young Boys midfielder is shown a yellow card.
Injury worry here for Mbappe as he signals that he cannot continue due to a problem and he has been replaced by Icardi.
Dimarco is shown a yellow card after tripping Bruno to halt a breakaway.
McTominay initially does well to step in and win the ball off Maehle, but then catches the wing-back in the face as he holds him off. He's shown the first yellow card of the game.

LILLE GO IN FRONT! The visitors have certainly looked a more aggressive proposition in this second half, and after Celik gets into the area from his right-flank station, his powerful strike rattles the post and falls to the feet of Ikone, who slots home Lille's second goal. The French champions go in front! 2-1 to Lille!

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!!! RUDIGER LEVELS THE TIE!!!!!!!!!! 2-0 CHELSEA ON THE NIGHT, 3-3 ON AGGREGATE!!!!!!! Chelsea are back in the tie as Rudiger directs a pinpoint header past Courtois. Mount swings a dangerous cross in from the right flank that sails into the middle. Rudiger attacks the delivery and places his effort with precision into the bottom-right corner. A perfect header.

GOAL! MANCHESTER CITY 3-2 RB LEIPZIG! City switch off at the back and get punished. It's Nkunku with the header again as he drifts into the box unmarked to get on the end of Olmo's cross. City have De Bruyne down near the centre circle but that's no excuse for the lapse in concentration.
Olmo's dinked cross was delightful but City should have defended that better. Leipzig are gaining more and more belief that they can turn this match around.
Joao Mario brings down Coman on the charge and goes into the book.
Chasing back to cover, Vidal chops down Jones just over 20 yards from goal and becomes the latest man into the book.
Mount adds an assist to his impressive night with a perfect cross for Rudiger to head home.

The visitors double their lead! It's Vinicius with the goal after a dinked effort over the keeper Trubin. It was Modric who played a superb ball into him and the Brazilian made no mistake with his finish.
Salzburg now make their first change with Wober replaced by Kamil Piatkowski.
Amorim made a change as that goal was disallowed, with Ugarte replacing Goncalves.
Cristiano makes another crucial interception; sadly for Sheriff, it is illegal, and he brings down Dumfries, and he picks up a card in the process.

GOAL!!! WHAT A HIT FROM PALOMINO!!! A long ball into the box is nodded down and then cushioned into the path of Palomino on the edge of the box. The defender thumps the ball at goal on the half-volley and rifles his shot into the back of the net! It's 2-1 to Atalanta!
Goal Arnaut Danjuma Adam Groeneveld
Assist Gerard Moreno Balaguero
Pasalic had his back to goal and was crowded out as the ball came to him - he made the right choice laying it off for Palomino instead of trying to take it under control himself.

HALLER HAT-TRICK - SPORTING 1-4 AJAX - Haller will be taking the match ball home with him after another fine counter-attack from Ajax. Just moments after Sporting had a goal disallowed, Ajax carved them open as Antony's pass with the outside of his foot picked out Haller. Yet again, the striker was in the right place at the right time, and he did the rest as he flicked the ball into the net.
Wendel can't continue, and Andrey Mostovoy comes on to replace him in the game's first change.
Militao goes in hard from behind on Mbappe and goes into the book.
Yilmaz is booked for the handball which has cost his side a penalty.
Antony gets his second official assist of the night, and he also played a huge part in the opening goal. Haller will get all the plaudits, but Antony has been deadly for Ajax.

GOALLL! THILL! SHERIFF EQUALISE! 1-1. Dimarco hauls over Bruno, presenting Sheriff with a promising free-kick 30 yards out. Thill -- who scored the winner against Madrid -- steps up and curls a sensational effort over the wall, beyond Handanovic and into the top corner!

THIAGO SCORES! And what a goal it was! Oxlade-Chamberlain's free-kick is a poor one, and it's cleared by Mbemba at the front of the crowd. It rolls out to Thiago, who is a long way out, and he hits it sweetly with the outside of his boot on the half-volley. It rockets past Costa, who can do nothing as it nestles into the bottom corner. 1-0 Liverpool!
Kondogbia gets a yellow card now. He was judged to have unfairly challenged with Taremi in the air.
Former Tottenham man Lamela comes on for Suso.
Sent off in the reverse fixture earlier this season, Guilavogui finds himself booked for a poorly timed tackle on Acuna in midfield.

OFF! Griezmann's eventful evening goes from the sublime to the ridiculous as he is shown a straight red card for a high boot on Firmino. He tries to gain possession for the ball in the air and lifts his foot. However, he catches Firmino straight on the side of his head and the referee does not hesitate in giving the forward his marching orders.
Muller's quick thinking helped create that chance, and he showed no signs of hesitation as he picked out Lewandowski with a sharp pass.
Sydorchuk is the first Dynamo player to be booked after he deliberately pulls Rafa to the ground to stop him from breaking into the final third.
Buyalskiy does well to get around the outside of Sarr, who tugs him back twice. He's booked after the Kiev midfielder goes down on the second occasion.
Joao Felix slid in on Fabinho to try and intercept the pass into Salah in the build-up to that chance. When the move comes to an end, the referee goes back and books him for the challenge.

GOAAALLLL - BAYERN 1-0 VILLAREAL - Lewandowski's first shot of the night finds the back of the net, and he punishes Parejo for a sloppy pass. The Villarreal midfielder gave possession away, and that allowed Muller to pounce. The German international picked out Lewandowski, and the Pole did the rest, slotting the ball home via the far post.

ANOTHER FOR REUS! Woeful Besiktas defending allows Dortmund to put together a slick short-passing move on the edge of the box, and Reus then dances through with some neat footwork to slot home calmly for his brace. Dortmund now lead Besiktas 3-0, and they look to be showing no mercy!

GOOOALLLL!!!! City have their third!!! It's Walker who rampages forward and plays a quick one-two with De Bruyne. The Belgian's pass back to him is perfectly weighted and Walker slides the ball underneath Mignolet, in very similar fashion to his opposite full-back's opener! 3-0 to City, and surely no way back for Brugge now.

That one-two between Walker and De Bruyne was just beautiful, and it's great to see both full-backs on the scoresheet as a showcase of how influential both Walker and Cancelo have been when linking up with their attacking team-mates.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!!! ESTUPINAN SCORES AN OWN GOAL!!!!!! 1-0 LIVERPOOL!!!! The Reds take the lead as Henderson's cross deflects off Estupinan and beats Rulli at his near post. Henderson is played into space by Salah down the right wing and looks to send a delivery into the middle. Estupinan sticks out a boot and inadvertently deflects it into the net as Rulli gets a hand to it, but cannot keep it out.

OFF! Ahmedhodzic is dismissed for deliberate handball after a VAR check. Kuzyaev latches on to a knockdown from Dzyuba and flicks the ball forward. It strikes the hand of Ahmedhodzic, preventing a goal-scoring opportunity for the hosts. The referee brandishes the red card after initially giving the defender a yellow following a consultation with the screen at the side of the pitch.
Rose has seen enough from Malen today, and Hazard is brought on in the Dutch striker's place. Not a happy return to his homeland for the former PSV man!
DAHLIN MAKES AMENDS! The penalty is saved. Dzyuba smashes his spot-kick down the middle, and -- despite diving to his right -- Dahlin is able to hook it to safety with his legs!
Lopetegui wastes no time in turning to his bench as Augustinsson makes way for Mir.
Dzyuba had to wait a long time to take that penalty, and it appears nerves got to him. The penalty was hit poorly down the middle and Dahlin had enough time to adjust and save it with his legs.
Danjuma has picked up where he left off in the first half and just breezes past Dalot again to get in behind and set up the goal.

RASHFORD PULLS ONE BACK! It's a poor pass from Zappacosta which gifts the ball to Fernandes through the middle and he plays a wonderful pass through to Rashford. He runs in behind the defence to latch onto it and Musso rushes off his line, but the forward curls his shot around him and into the far post. 2-1!
Involved in an attractive move in the attacking third, Dahoud's was the pass which allowed Reus to dribble clear and roll home the third.
Fernandes spotted the loose pass and played a wonderful first-time ball between Atalanta's defenders to pick out Rashford's run.
Moumi Ngamaleu follows his team-mate into the book, catching Parejo as he tried to win the ball back following a slaloming dribble through the centre.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!! FODEN SCORES THIS TIME!!!!!!! 3-1 CITY!!!!!!!!! Foden was denied by Carvajal on the line five minutes ago, but this time he finds the back of the net with an inch-perfect header. Fernandinho surges down the right flank and lifts a perfect cross into the middle. Foden drifts between Militao and Carvajal to guide his header into the bottom-right corner.

ALCACER SCORES! Danjuma gets away from Dalot down the left again and the right-back can't intercept the pass into him. He pulls it back for Alcacer, who sticks out a leg to poke it past De Gea and into the back of the net. 1-0 Villarreal!
It's a yellow card for Christiansen and Mount will take this free-kick. Let's see if he can do better than his previous attempt in the first half.
ADEYEMI AGAIN! 2-0! Salzburg double their advantage. Adeyemi steps up confidently and rolls it down the middle and into the net as Grbic dives to his left!
Rakitic is sent on for Mir as the visitors try and get back into this game.
Fernandinho produces a great burst down the right flank before floating a sublime cross into the box for Foden to attack and score.
Dimarco is replaced by Bastoni immediately after the goal.
On that occasion, Sane could have gone for goal, but his simple pass bamboozled the visitors, and Muller did the rest.
The bookings are flowing thick and fast now and Gaspar is third player in four minutes to get a yellow card as he trips Moumi Ngamaleu in a dangerous position on the wing.
Pepe limps off to be replaced by Marcano in defence.

GOAAALLLL - SHERIFF 0-1 INTER - Inzaghi's side finally break the deadlock, and Vidal and Brozovic combine in devastating fashion. The Chile international teed up his fellow midfielder on the edge of the box, and Brozovic did the rest. First, he beat two players before smashing the ball into the bottom corner past Athanasiadis, and it is no more than Inter deserve.
Alvarez puts an arm across Esgaio to stop his run, and he's shown a yellow card.
Pep Guardiola introduces the first of his substitutes, as the more attacking Gabriel Jesus comes on for Zinchenko.

GOAL! MANCHESTER CITY 2-1 CLUB BRUGGE! Seconds after City almost go behind, they go ahead. Mahrez's ball from the right is slowly collected by Cancelo. Cancelo has all the time in the world to pick his cross and return it to Mahrez. The Algerian nods in at the far post.
That was superb vision from Vidal, who could have gone for goal himself, but he picked out Brozovic, who was the better option.
Adeyemi is shown a yellow card after excitedly running into the crowd to celebrate.
Chiesa looks to nip around the outside of Lovren, but the Zenit captain stands his ground and blocks the run of the Juventus winger. He's booked for the foul and the home side have a free-kick.
D'Ambrosio gets the game's first yellow card for stepping on Vinicius' heel as Madrid break through midfield.
Brugge went to sleep temporarily and Cancelo punished them for it. The Portuguese left-back is making his mark on this game for City.

It's 1-1! It's yet another goal for Haller as Tagliafico is played through by Martinez. The full-back beats Gunok to the ball and toes it across to Haller, and the French striker is able to finish into an empty net to get Ajax level.
Garcia picks up a yellow card for a poor challenge on Rafa. Garcia thrashes his arms in frustration.

GOAAALLL - BAYERN 5-0 SALZBURG - Salzburg's resolve is broken again in the second half, and Muller grabs his first of the evening. Naglesmann's side worked their way through the Salzburg midfield, with Sane picking out Muller in the penalty box. The veteran turned onto his left foot and smashed the ball home, and he made it look effortless!
Substitution Marten Elco de Roon Luis Fernando Muriel Fruto
It was a superb run by Tagliafico and Martinez was able to find him. The Argentinian man just managed to get to the ball before Gunok to send it to Haller to score.
The second change of the pair sees Dzeko replaced up front by Correa as Inzaghi adds fresh legs to the forward line.
Capoue is fuming with a booking but it is one challenge too m any to go without a card for the Villarreal man now and he sees yellow.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!!!! MANE POKES HOME A SECOND FOR LIVERPOOL!!!!!!! 2-0!!!!!!!!! The Reds get a quick-fire double as Mane collects Salah's throughball before beating Rulli with a low strike. Salah weaves his way into the Villarreal box before sliding an offload through for the run of his team-mate. Mane gets there ahead of Rulli and finds the bottom-right corner with his strike.
Salah pushes the Villarreal defence back before sending a perfectly-weighted pass for Mane to collect and score.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!! JAMES BLASTS HOME A STRIKE!!!!!! 2-0 CHELSEA!!!!!! The Blues extend their lead as James fires a crisp strike past Szczesny. The wing-back gathers a cross from Ziyech in the right-inside channel before he lines up a drive. His effort rockets into the bottom-left corner to hand Chelsea control of the contest.
Wendel is booked after shoving Innocent off the ball.
Inzaghi wastes no time in bringing new faces on in search of a winning goal. Holding midfielder Brozovic is the first to come off, with attacking midfielder Calhanoglu replacing him.

Ronaldo is chasing down a long ball and Lovato is trying to catch it as well. It's clumsy from the substitute as he clatters into the back of Ronaldo, but he wasn't through on goal, so it's only a yellow card for Lovato.
Guilavogui is booked after a late challenge on Xeka near the touchline.
Dimarco enters the action for the home side on the left flank to replace Perisic.
Well placed to capitalise on the opportunity, Jota crossed for Firmino to score.
Meunier swings his boot at a ball dropping over his shoulder and catches N'Sakala, earning himself a yellow card.
Le Ketelaere collects a diagonal ball from Balanta, and does even better to get around Kehrer, who brings down the Brugge striker and is booked.
Tomori goes through the back of Taremi as the centre-back looks to get alongside the forward. However, the Englishman oversteps the mark and becomes the first Milan player in the book.

LIVERPOOL LEAD AGAIN! Putting his side three goals in front on aggregate, Firmino takes advantage of an error by Vlachodimos, whose mistake ultimately sees the ball fall to Jota. The Portugal international then crosses for his Brazilian colleague to tap home from close range! It's 2-1 to Liverpool; 5-2 overall!

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!!!!! VINICIUS STRIKES BACK FOR MADRID!!!!!!!! 3-2!!!!! The Brazilian speeds away from Fernandinho before beating Ederson with a low finish from the inside-left channel. Fernandinho gets too tight to Vinicius, who leaves him in his wake down the left flank. No City player goes across to the forward and as a result he has time to find the back of the net with a composed finish.
Yansane makes his way on to the pitch to replace Kolovos.
Dumfries makes his way on to the field to replace Darmian down the right flank.
Palhinha mistimes his sliding challenge on Bellingham and catches the youngster from the wrong side. The Sporting midfielder earns himself a yellow card as a result.
GOAL! SHERIFF 0-3 REAL MADRID! Madrid are cruising to victory. Benzema receives a pass from Mendy and slots into the bottom left corner from the edge of the box.
Mendy had too much time on the ball there and he has made Sheriff pay. It's clear that there'll be no upset on this occasion.
Larsson picks up a yellow card for his blatant foul on Rudiger. There's a short delay before the penalty's taken.
Rakip is withdrawn for the visitors and is replaced by Olsson. Tomasson attempts to shore up his backline after the Ahmedhodzic dismissal.
Paredes gets to a loose ball ahead of Rodri and is caught immediately by the City midfielder, who subsequently receives the first booking of the game.

GOAL!!!!! ORIGI HEADS HOME!!! IT'S 2-1 TO LIVERPOOL!!! The Reds deal a massive blow to Milan's last-16 hopes as Origi heads in on the rebound. Tomori loses possession on the edge of his own box to Mane, who surges into the box before firing at goal. Maignan makes a fine reaction save, but the ball loops towards Origi. The Belgian directs his header away from the Milan keeper into the top-right corner.
Mendy releases the run of Vinicius down the left flank and the forward does the rest with a great finish.

GOOOOOOAL! 4-0 SPORTING! Sarabia gets in on the act as he turns home with into an empty net from near the penalty spot. Reis' initial run causes chaos at the back for the visitors and Welinton can only clear as far as the loanee, who pokes into the back of the net with his right foot with Destanoglu on the floor.
The other change by the hosts sees Uribe replaced by Vitinha.
That was some assist by Hudson-Odoi who got the chance to put his pace to use there. Chelsea will be relieved to have gained the lead.
Hermoso departs with Lodi taking his place.
Porto have made a double change now, with Sanusi the first to come off and he has been replaced by Wendell.
Joao Felix is replaced by Griezmann in attack.

It's quite brilliant from Vinicius who makes it 3-0! He does superbly to weave his way into the box and shift onto his left foot, before driving his effort into the back of the net. That is surely the goal that finishes this game off.
Rafa is next in the referee's book as he slides in unfairly on Pedri.
Atletico make a triple substitution - Simeone is clearly unhappy with their performance. The first change sees Koke make way for Correa.
Benzema laid it into the feet of Vinicius whose individual brilliance has put this game surely beyond the reaches of their opponents.

GOAL! MALMO FF 0-1 CHELSEA! Chelsea break Malmo's resistance! It's a lovely goal as Hudson-Odoi plays a round-the-corner pass to Havertz and races onto the return. The winger's fizzed cross finds Ziyech at the far post who slots home from close range.

GOALLL! GRIEZMANN! 1-0. Atletico take the lead against the run of play. Lemar swings in a dangerous corner and it flicks off Taremi, carrying it all the way through to the back post, where Griezmann taps in under no pressure from close range!
Referee Slavko Vincic took his time, but he decided that the challenge on Ulmer from Jordan was worthy of a yellow card.
Second change for Atalanta now as Zapata comes on to replace Muriel.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!! LEWANDOWSKI SCORES ON THE REBOUND!!!!!! 2-0 BAYERN!!!!! The German side double their advantage as Lewandowski is alert from close range to poke the ball home after Musiala strikes the post. Bayern play their way through Barca in the middle of the park before Musiala latches on to a blocked strike. He hammers an effort towards goal that clatters off the right post. Lewandowski is first to react and stretches out his left boot to knock into an empty net.
Rits is withdrawn for Brugge's first change of the night, and Ruud Vormer replaces him.
Sowah has run his socks off to no avail in this match, and he's replaced by Ignace van der Brempt.
event_player: [' I. Van der Brempt ', ' K. Sowah ']

comment: That move started with a direct pass by Dias who spotted Grealish in space. City's captain for the day has contributed to the goal of the game so far.
Ahmedhodzic is booked for his part in the protests towards the referee following Wendel's shove on Innocent.

GOAL! MANCHESTER CITY 4-2 RB LEIPZIG! Grealish restores City's two-goal advantage with a lovely strike! The Englishman drives inside from the left flank and curls past Gulacsi with a swish of his right foot. Leipzig knew it was coming but could do nothing about it.
It's a good ball over the top from Palomino that just takes Wan-Bissaka out of the game and gets Zapata in behind United.

ZAPATA SCORES! It's another lovely ball lifted over the top by Palomino to pick out Zapata's run inside from the left, and he's one-on-one with De Gea. Maguire rushes back but can't get there before the forward lifts his shot over De Gea and into the back of the net. The offside flag goes up, but after a VAR check, the goal stands! 2-1 Atalanta!
Upamecano brings down Yaremchuk in the final third, handing Benfica a free-kick in a useful position.
With the tie all but wrapped up, Klopp makes some changes. First, Jota is replaced by Salah.
Sheriff make the game's first change. Their goalscorer Yakhshiboev, who took a while to get up after miscontrolling his chance earlier, makes way for Bruno.
GOAL! CHELSEA 4-0 MALMO! Jorginho steps up and grabs his second goal of the game, firing high into the centre of the goal. Diawara had no chance of reaching the shot.
Sandra comes off in Brugge's first change, and replacing him is Ignace Van der Brempt.
event_player: [' I. Van der Brempt ', ' C. Sandra ']

comment: Pasalic clips McTominay as the midfielder spins away from him and he's shown a yellow card.

WIDE!!! Dybala steps up and smashes his penalty to the wrong aside of the right-hand post!!! It's an awful strike, but the referee is ordering a re-take!!! Kritsyuk was off his line at the time of the shot, so Dybala will step up again...
Malmo respond to going behind by making changes. Olsson replaces Rieks at left wing-back.
Stretching for an outswinging Tadic cross, Haller just managed to get a head on the ball, which diverted it to Antony's feet, for the winger to work his magic.

ANOTHER FOR AJAX! This time Antony gets it right! The elusive Brazilian collects a flicked header from Haller on the right side of the area, stands Can up and then proceeds to whip the ball around the static German defender and into the far corner of the Dortmund net - a delicious strike! Ajax have their three-goal lead: 3-0 to the Dutch champions!
Substitution Francis Coquelin Alfonso Pedraza Sag
Asensio has been ineffectual in the final third this evening and is withdrawn for the home side.
Ilkay Gundogan is also brought on, in place of the impressive Bernardo Silva.
Yellow Card Daniel Parejo Munoz
The goal scorer, Leao, is also being taken off, with Giroud on in his place.
Yellow Card Alberto Moreno Perez
Lopetegui is not hanging about here! Suso is coming off for Jordan - the first of three changes for Sevilla.
Camavinga enters the action for Kroos in the middle of the park, who still may be struggling with an injury.
The booked Laporte is replaced by Nathan Ake in City's first change of the match.
Having conceded the penalty which turned the trajectory of this game, Delaney is withdrawn for Lamela to get half an hour to change the game.

GOOOALLLL!!!! What a move from Leipzig!!! It's Angelino again down the left and although this cross, which was perfectly weighted, beats Silva, Mukiele is on hand to volley past Navas and put Leipzig ahead 2-1!!! What a game this is turning out to be!!!

The horizontal movement across the pitch from Leipzig's midfielders is causing PSG all sorts of problems. It's no wonder Angelino is experiencing such freedom down the left given how many other forward runners that Hakimi is having to worry about, and the Spain left-back was on hand yet again to see another perfect cross directed goalwards!
Diaz has gone down, and it looks like he's got a muscle injury. The players gesture straight to the bench and Ballo-Toure is on to replace him.
Mendy catches Danilo on the ankle with a late boot and goes into the book.
Rekik does indeed come off for Jordan.
Mir has been only an intermittent presence up front for the hosts, and is now replaced by En-Nesyri.
The yellow card is out again, this time for De Roon as he clumsily brings down Shaw from behind to stop his run.
Juventus make their first change now as Juan Cuadrado replaces Alex Sandro.
Angelino becomes the next Leipzig player in the book for bringing down De Bruyne.
Milan are making a triple change here and Ballo-Toure is the first to make way, with Kalulu coming on to replace him.
Ibrahimovic is also being brought on in place of Giroud.
Thiago will provide the third pair of fresh legs for the home side, as he comes on for Milner.
Wolf is forced off due to injury and is replaced at left-back by Passlack.
Juventus make their third change now as Arthur replaces Manuel Locatelli.
Liverpool captain Henderson makes way for Fabinho in midfield.
And Tomori is the last to make way, with Romagnoli on for him.
Coates dragged Malen back in the build-up to his deflected effort and the referee plays advantage before going back to book the centre-back retrospectively.
Juventus make their second change now as Dejan Kulusevski replaces Federico Bernardeschi.

GOAAAALLLL - SPORTING 0-5 MAN CITY - Oh my word. Sterling scores City's fifth of the night, and that is the pick of them, so far. The Sporting defence stood off him for a split second, and before they could react, Sterling whipped his shot into the far corner, leaving Adan with no chance in goal. If there was a ball-shaped hole in the net, Sterling's effort would have found it. Ludicrously good from the City forward.
Loftus-Cheek collects an offload from James and twists and turns in the box. He spots Hudson-Odoi in space before teeing up his team-mate to score.
De Ligt is the first Juve man in the referee's book, having been cautioned for a foul on Rakip.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!!! HUDSON-ODOI MAKES IT THREE!!!!!! 3-0 CHELSEA!!!!! The Blues surely put the game out of Juve's reach as Hudson-Odoi slams home a strike from close range. James takes possession in the right-inside channel and feeds Loftus-Cheek on the charge through the middle. He cannot find space for a shot, but he offloads for Hudson-Odoi to fire past Szczesny on his left foot.
The first yellow card of the game goes to Thiago, who cynically hacks Silva down before the winger can escape down the right wing.

GOAL! Vidal restores Inter's lead! 2-1. Barella finds Dzeko on the edge of the box and the striker draws in a defender before releasing Vidal who squeezes in a low strike at the near post from eight yards!
It was a wonderful assist from Dzeko. He held it up and drew in the defence, before picking out Vidal with a precise, low pass and the midfielder did the rest!
Villarreal are making the first change of the game here as the goal scorer, Alcacer, goes off for Dia.
Amorim has opted to make a change in pursuit of a point, with Tomas coming off and Nuno Santos on in his place.
His match ended by injury, Botman makes way for Onana.
Ghezzal is shown a yellow card after lunging in late on Matheus inside the Sporting half.
Malmo's captain Christiansen is next to go off. The Bosnian attacking midfielder Nalic replaces him.

NERES SCORES! Santos slips on the ball and Schuurs is there to set Ajax on the counter. He slides it through to Neres, who is in so much space on the left of the box. Virginia rushes off his line to close him down, but the forward slots his shot under him and into the back of the net. 3-1 Ajax!
Schuurs got lucky as Santos slipped on the ball, but then he did well to pick out Neres' run to set up the goal.
Szoboszlai is substituted off for Silva.
Pena also heads off. Lewicki takes his place in Malmo's midfield.
Mostovoy has been one of Zenit's best, but he's withdrawn for Daniil Krugovoy..

GOOOALLLL!!! He makes no mistake this time!!! Dybala steps up once more and shoots to the same side. Kristyuk guesses right but it's tucked right into the corner and the Zenit keeper can't keep it out! 2-1 to Juve, and they're back in control of this match!
Erik Lamela replaces Gomez in Sevilla's latest change now.
Sarabia comes off for Sporting, and is replaced by Marcus Edwards.
Lille make another defensive change, as Celik is taken off for the more attacking option of Weah.
Celik is booked for dragging down Ocampos on the touchline.
Malmo respond to conceding again by making more changes. Rakip takes Pena's place in midfield first.
Sheriff decide that changes are needed. Bruno goes off first. Their Trinidian left-sided player Julien comes on.
Coquelin could have put the Spanish side in control of the tie, but he was caught offside to deny Villarreal a second. He is now withdrawn for Pedraza down the left flank.
Teixeira makes way for Bozdogan as Yalcin looks to halt the Dutch side's comeback.
Bennacer enters the action to replace Diaz in the Milan midfield.
And the assist is Schuurs' last action, with Rensch on for him.
Dybala enters the action for the visitors as he replaces Bentancur. It appears too little too late for Juve.
Double change for Salzburg now, with Sucic the first to make way, with Capaldo replacing him.
And Sesko is also being taken off, with Adamu on for him.
Pizzi is replaced by Everton in midfield as Benfica search for an injection of energy.
Benfica decide now's the right time to make changes. The Uruguayan striker Nunez replaces Yaremchuk up front.
The booked Joao Mario also heads off. Taarabt takes his place in midfield for Benfica.
Foyth is carded after a late challenge on Coman while trying to block a cross.
Valverde sprinted clear down the right before splitting the Liverpool defence with a low cross to pick out Vinicius' far-post run.
Elliott created history for the Reds by becoming their youngest Champions League starter tonight. He is now withdrawn for Keita.
Mane is withdrawn by Klopp as Diaz enters the field to replace the forward in the final third.
Double change for Atletico now and that disallowed goal was Suarez's last involvement as he's replaced by Herrera.
And Joao Felix is also being taken off, with Lodi on in his place.
Second change for Liverpool now. Fabinho, who's just coming back from injury is taken off, with Thiago, who is returning from his own spell on the sidelines, coming on for him.
The first Leipzig substitution sees Forsberg come off and he has been replaced by Szoboszlai.
Meanwhile the other change sees Silva replaced by Poulsen.
Karavaev, who set up the own goal, comes off for Brazil international Malcom.
Emery makes a double-change as he looks to hold what he has. The quiet Pino comes off for Trigueros.
Bernardo adds an assist to his two goals for the night.
Saelemaekers replaces Tonali to add an extra dimension in the final third.

REAL MADRID LEAD! Sneaking in behind Alexander-Arnold, the ever-alert Vinicius fires home at the back post to give Madrid a 1-0 lead just before the hour mark! Excellent work from Valverde down the right was rewarded by the Brazilian's well-timed run and cool finish from the left side of the six-yard box.
Gomes makes way for Bamba following that injury.
The other change by the visitors sees Yaremchuk replaced by Nunez.
City make their first round of substitutions. Fernandinho replaces Rodri at the base of City's midfield.
Bernardo Silva also heads off. Gundogan will take his place in central midfield.
Hummels apparently takes retribution on Matheus with a late challenge of his own, which sees the centre-back shown a yellow card.
Benfica have made a triple substitution now, with Everton the first man to come off and he has been replaced by Radonjic.
Malmo are seeking fresh momentum, so throw on Nalic for Rakip, who has been overrun in midfield today.
Birmancevic is brought off now, with Abubakari on in his place.
Busquets is withdrawn by Koeman and is replaced Gavi.
Demir enters the action for the home side in place of Sergi Roberto.
Gilberto is another to come off for Benfica and he has been replaced by Lazaro.
Hernandez pulls back Rafa on a run down the right flank and goes into the book.

Milner rises with Trippier and catches the full-back with a stray arm across the chest. Atletico appeal for a red card, but the referee brandishes a yellow. Even the yellow appears to be a harsh decision.
Greenwood is tripped by Trigueros and Villarreal aren't happy with the free-kick that's given. Moreno kicks the ball away and is booked for dissent.
Calhanoglu is last to leave the pitch for now. Vecino is Inter's latest addition.

GOALLLL!!!! The hosts are back in front! Arnold sends a lofted ball over to Lukas Nmecha, and the striker brings it down on his chest before smashing a brilliant finish past the diving Kohn. It's a clinical effort, and his side now lead 2-1.
It's a brilliant assist by Arnold as his through ball allowed Lukas Nmecha to bring it down and fire home.
Dynamo have also made a substitution now, with Shkurin heading off and he has been replaced by Harmash.
Henderson replaces Fabinho in the middle of the park and immediately takes the armband from Van Dijk.
Bayern are making their first change now, and it's Tolisso that's making way for Roca.
And Tomas is the other player making way, with Peto replacing him.
There's a double change for both sides now, starting with Ajax. That goal was Neres' last involvement as he's replaced by Klaassen.
Tonali overruns the ball and fouls Felipe in his attempts to keep it. The substitute then walks away with the ball and Kondogbia pushes him to the ground in frustration.
Saul replaces Ziyech for the home side in the final third, notably ahead of Werner and Mount.

GOAL! Salah scores his second of the game and Liverpool's third! Jones does brilliantly in midfield, winning the ball back on the halfway line and then breaking forward quickly, before laying it out to Salah to his right, who only had Costa to beat and he coolly slides it past the keeper and into the back of the net.
Inzaghi isn't happy with Inter's start to this half. They're making a triple change. Brozovic is first to go. Vidal takes his place in midfield.
Dzeko is surprisingly sacrificed too by Inter. The former Barcelona forward Sanchez takes his place up front.
For Sporting, Santos goes off, with Paulinho on in his place.

Jones has now been involved in two Liverpools goals today and he set up that one perfectly. Sprinting forward, opening up the Porto defence, before spotting Salah in space and picking the right pass. Salah then did the rest with a composed finish.
Castaneda is next to make way. Sheriff's Guinean centre-forward Yansane comes on.
Arthur has hardly been on the pitch that long but he picks up a yellow for a particularly indulgent challenge now. Juventus need to watch their own temper as much as Zenit do.
Matheus makes way as Amorim sends on Braganca in midfield.
The Sporting head coach also brings on Santos for Paulinho.
Carvajal blocks off the run of Mbappe down the left flank and goes into the book. The epitome of taking one for the team there.
Lille make a triple substitution as they look to find a way back into this game. The first change sees Xeka make way for Onana in midfield.
Simeone's third substitution sees Matheus Cunha enter the game, with Llorente the one to make way.
There's also a fresh set of legs up front as Angel Correa replaces Griezmann.
Interesting tactics from Simeone as he makes three changes, with Koke the first to be replaced, with Rodrigo De Paul now on in his place.

TELLES SCORES! Fernandes takes the free-kick on the edge of the box on the right and pulls it back for Telles, who is hovering just outside the area. He lets it drop and hits it sweetly on the volley, curling it through the crowd and into the bottom corner. 1-1!
Lindelof grabs Joao Felix's arm to tug him back and stop the run and he's shown a yellow card.
It's a well-worked free-kick from Fernandes and he plays a perfectly weighted cross into Telles from the free-kick.
Trigueros is replaced by Moi Gomez for the Yellow Submarine too.
Clement turns to his bench for a third time, with Mechele on in place of Der Brempt.
event_player: [' B. Mechele ', ' I. Van der Brempt ']

comment: Llorente pulls back Hernandez down the Milan left flank and goes into the book.
Hernandez applauds the crowd for their support as he makes way for Upamecano.
Leipzig's summer signing Andre Silva also makes way. Poulsen takes his place up top.
Leipzig also want to make a few changes. Laimer goes off. Haidara comes on.
A crude attempt at earning a penalty by simulation only gets En-Nesyri a yellow card for diving. Not the immediate impact he had in mind!
Kolovos is last to head off for now after an ineffectual hour. Nikolov is Sheriff's third introduction to the game.
Capoue makes way for Francis Coquelin in a Villarreal change now.
Zenit make their first change now as Sardar Azmoun replaces Artem Dzyuba.
Madrid make their first change of the game. Marcelo replaces Mendy at left-back.
Lovren brings down Werner as he looks to turn on the edge of the box, and is yellow carded as Chelsea gain a free-kick from a dangerous position.
Alaba brings down Dzeko in the final third with a loose challenge and goes into the book.
Santos' night is over, with Tomas making his way onto the field.
Jaissle makes two changes in the final third as Chukwubuike is replaced by Kjaergaard.
Atalanta make a swap too, with Djimsiti off and Merih Demiral on.
Sane could have gone for goal himself as he was in a decent position on the edge of the box, but was unselfish and played it to Lewandowski, who coolly converted.

GOAL! LEWANDOWSKI MAKES IT 4-1! The striker scores his second of the game to put the finishing touch on a superb Bayern counter-attack! Kimmich picks Sane out in behind and he then lays it off to Lewandowski to his left, who takes a touch and then chips the ball over Vlachodimos and into the back of the net.
Zinchenko is now also on the pitch, with Stones making way. That now means Cancelo will move over to right-back!
Vinicius pounces on the loose ball after Donnarumma's mistake and picks out Benzema to score from six yards.
PSG make their first change, as Georginio Wijnaldum is introduced in place of Herrera.
Gueye is also withdrawn, replaced by Danilo Pereira.
Atletico are making another change now as Simeone brings on Griezmann for Koke.
Aebischer is the latest entrant into the referee's book after a poor challenge on Trigueros, who has been on the pitch for just two minutes.
Ziyech stretches and catches Chiesa with a late challenge. He goes into the book.
Herrera can't carry on, and Danilo Pereira comes on in his place.
N'Soki is fouled and wins a free-kick, which Lang takes before the referee's whistle. He's booked for that indiscretion, which is soft to say the least.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!! DONNARUMMA HANDS MADRID A LIFELINE AS BENZEMA SCORES!!!!!!!! 1-1!!!!!! The Italy keeper makes a terrible mistake at the back and presents Benzema with an easy chance to convert from close range. Donnarumma takes a backpass from Verratti and hangs on to it for far too long. Benzema closes him down and the loose ball travels to Vinicius. The Brazilian squares to Benzema, who places his effort into the bottom-left corner away from Donnarumma's desperate lunge.
Meanwhile, Firmino replaces Mane in Liverpool's third substitution, as the visitors refresh their attacking lineup.

INTER LEAD! This tie is back in the balance! Martinez makes light of his quiet showing so far, taking a couple of touches to position himself on the left corner of the box before unleashing an unstoppable shot into the top corner. What a strike! Liverpool 0-1 Inter, and now only 2-1 on aggregate!
Forsberg is next to go off for Leipzig. The Swede's definitely impacted the game. Szoboszlai is his replacement.
De Pena is replaced by Vintinho down the left flank for the visitors.
It's the skipper Henderson who enters the action first for Liverpool, replacing Thiago as Klopp tries to regain control of the midfield.
Jota is also on, replacing Salah, who hasn't been too heavily involved for Klopp's men.
Having been the livelier of Inter's front pairing, Sanchez played in his partner Martinez to strike from distance.
Larin also makes way for Bozdogan.
Dia is subbed out for Arnaut Danjuma Groeneveld by Unai Emery and the hosts.

GOAAALLL - REAL MADRID 2-1 SHAKHTAR DONETSK - He's done it again. Sheer class from Benzema and the build-up play was just as good. One-touch football galore from Ancelotti and Shakhtar were helpless as Vinicius Jr picked out Benzema. The former Lyon frontman was ready to pounce on the edge near the penalty spot, and he fired past Trubin with ease. Sublime play from the home side!
Steffen is replaced by Waldschmidt for the second Wolfsburg change.
Yalcin makes his first change of the evening, replacing Larin with Karaman as he looks to get his side back into the game.
Darmian claims the assist, and he will be grateful after seeing his original shot blocked by the Shakhtar defence.

GOOOOOOALLLL! MILAN MAKE IT 1-1! The hosts take their time over the free-kick, which is subsequently blocked by the wall. Giroud keeps the chance alive with an acrobatic effort that Costa parries. Kalulu, however, is there to slide through the goalkeeper's legs and the ball eventually goes into the back of the net as Mbemba pokes into his own goal.
Zenit make their second change now as Aleksey Sutormin replaces Vyacheslav Karavaev.
Second change for Villarreal now, and it's Trigueros that's making way for Estupinan.
Diaz is giving Jota no space as he closes the forward down and he's shown a yellow card after clipping the back of his heels.
For the second time tonight, Vinicius Jr sets up Benzema inside the penalty area.

GOAAALLL!!!! INTER 1-0 SHAKHTAR - Finally, the deadlock is broken as Dzeko thumps the ball into the bottom corner. Inter charged their way down the left-hand side, with Perisic then able to pick out Darmian at the far post. The right-back had his half-volley blocked, but the ball rebounded to Dzeko. The former Roma man took a second to pick his spot before curling the ball into the goal past Trubin.
Guardiola starts to look after his players, with Foden making way for Gundogan.
Supriah is withdrawn after an ineffectual performance and is replaced by Harmash.
Hutchinson is the next man to make way for Yalcin's men as Ucan comes on in the middle of the park.
Kolovos is carded after a poor challenge, joining team-mate Cristiano in the book.
Mengi replaces Shaw at left-back for the home side.
Wolfsburg make a double change as they look to change the momentum of this game. The first change sees Baku make way for Lukebakio in attack.
Mbabu makes way for Lukas Nmecha.
It was a good build-up from Ajax and Klaassen kept it moving along quickly as he picked out Berghuis.

BERGHUIS SCORES! Ajax are running away with this one now! Antony lays it off to Klaassen, who turns before spreading it out to Berghuis on the right of the box. His low shot takes a couple of deflections on the way through which catch out Virginia at the near post and Ajax are 4-1 up!
Haidara limps off for Leipzig having picked up a slight knock; Ilaix Moriba comes on in his place.
Arnold is the latest player to be flashed a yellow card after getting wrapped up in a challenge on David.
Cristiano raids down the left flank and delivers a perfect cross for Yansane to head past Pyatov.
Youngster Sesko is also given a chance, with Adeyemi taking his place on the bench.
Having made little impact, Wolf comes off to be replaced by Passlack.
Lo Celso brings down Robertson on the charge and goes into the book. Liverpool have a free-kick in a useful position.
The first change of the night sees Everton replaced by Ukraine international Yaremchuk.
Chistyakov catches Colak with a flailing arm and is shown a yellow card.
Mount flicks the ball past Rakitskiy before turning the defender, who sticks out a leg to trip him. He gives away a free-kick in a dangerous position and earns a yellow card.
Grimaldo sticks a foot out and commits a late challenge on Busquets. The referee responds by whipping out his yellow card.
Mane is withdrawn for the visitors and is replaced by Jota in the final third.
Saelemaekers is also going off, with Florenzi on to replace him.
Loftus-Cheek replaces Jorginho in the middle of the park.

GOOOOALLLLL!!!! CHELSEA EQUALISE!!! It's a great passage of play from Chelsea as Werner and Barkley play a great one-two on the edge of the box. It comes back to Werner, who tees up Lukaku to tap into an empty net! We're back on level terms again at 2-2!

FABINHO!!! 3-2 LIVERPOOL ON AGGREGATE! The Reds regain the advantage in the tie. Fabinho beats the offside trap to latch onto Salah's prodded throughball, before drilling a low shot through the legs of Rulli from a tight angle.
Salah timed his throughball perfectly and Fabinho took full advantage.
SAVE! Courtois is having a fine game and he puts the icing on the cake with a brilliant save to deny Messi. He dives to his left to turn a tame strike from the Argentine wide of the post.
Mendes is shown a yellow card for a poor challenge on Adams down the left wing. The second PSG player to be booked.
Poor challenge by Lang on Herrera, catching the PSG midfielder late and the referee shows no hesitation in showing him a yellow card.
Milan are making a double change here and Leao is the first to go off, with Giroud on for him.
Danilo brings down Vinicius on the charge and goes into the book.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!!! SHERIFF SCORE AGAINST THE RUN OF PLAY!!! YANSANE HEADS HOME!!!!! 2-0!!!! The home side double their advantage, stunning Shakhtar on the counter as Yansane rises to head an effort into the back of the net. Cristiano finds space down the left flank and delivers a perfect cross into the box. Yansane is left unmarked and he directs his header away from Pyatov into the top-left corner with precision.
MISS! Messi fails from the spot as he fires a poor left-footed strike at goal, and Courtois guesses the correct way to make the save. Frustration for the home side.
Radeljic makes his third appearance in the Champions League from the bench as he replaces Addo.
Aebischer is withdrawn for the visitors and is replaced by Sierro.
The goalscorer Rieder is replaced by Hefti in the middle of the park.
Okafor makes way for Sesko in attack for Salzburg.
Kanga enters the action to replace Siebatcheu as the Young Boys spearhead.
As one of Leipzig's holding midfielders, we have barely had to mention Laimer. He is now replaced by Moriba.
There's also a change at the back for RB Leipzig, with Klostermann making way for Henrichs.
Donnarumma goes into the book for dissent after claiming he was fouled by Benzema.
Gnabry is withdrawn for the visitors in the final third and is replaced by Sane.
Muller was ineffective in the final third tonight and is replaced by Goretzka.
Young Boys make the game's first change, as Silvan Hefti comes on for Lefort.

MUSIALA SCORES! Just moments after Barca created a good chance at the other end, they find themselves 3-0 down! Davies wrongfoots Araujo and pulls it back from the byline for Musiala. He's unmarked in the middle, and he passes it into the far bottom corner.
Davies is just too fast for Araujo and the left-back did well to keep the ball in play before he cut it back for Musiala.
Hudson-Odoi enters the action to replace Ziyech in the final third.
A crunching challenge by Fabinho on Valverde is mistimed; sending the latter flying into the air. The Liverpool midfielder receives the final's first booking as a result.

YILMAZ! 2-1! Game on as Lille pull a goal back! The visitors win a free-kick on the edge of the box, but at a tight angle. Yilmaz steps up and fizzes a powerful strike over the wall towards the near post, and it bounces just before Kohn who makes a mess of the shot. The goalkeeper attempts to push it clear, but it sneaks through his hands and into the back of the net!
Innocent is withdrawn for Pena in the Malmo midfield.
Lukaku looked like he might be offside, but that passing sequence from Werner and Barkley was just sublime and made it the easiest of finishes for the Chelsea striker.
Sesko replaces Adeyemi.
Frustration boils over for Alexander-Arnold as he kicks the ball away after being adjudged to have handled the ball. A needless one from the full-back.
Demiral hauls Siebatcheu back to prevent him from sprinting after a long ball forward on the counter and receives a yellow card for his trouble.
Chelsea are making the first change of the game just before the free-kick is taken. It's Ziyech that's going off, with Havertz on to replace him.
Laimer's had a much quieter second half, so he's taken off and replaced by Adams.

Jesus gets the assist, but the pass and run from Rodri and Walker respectively were the architects of that equaliser. The crowd's lifted too with that goal and this game just continues to electrify more and more.
Lang is shown the first yellow card of the night after a poor challenge on Gvardiol.
Reinildo sticks an arm across Pogba's chest to stop his bursting run down the right. He gives away a free-kick and has his name taken by the referee.
Weghorst makes way for Lukebakio.
Oxlader-Chamberlain replaces Milner as Klopp aims to avoid a potential dismissal for the veteran midfielder.
Reus will not complete his hat-trick, as he makes way for Haaland to make his Champions League comeback.

GOOOOALLLL!!! Finally, City have their goal!!! Walker shoots forward and Rodri finds him, before crossing on the volley across the face of goal. It's through the legs of Jesus, and Sterling is there to tap it into the far corner to level the scores at 1-1!!! What a game we have going on here!
Abubakari makes his way on to the field to replace Colak.

HALLER HAS FOUR!!!! SPORTING 1-5 AJAX - Haller take a bow! The Ajax frontman takes his tally to four for the night, and he continues to make every single finish look incredibly easy. This time it was Mazraoui's turn to be the provider, and his powerful throughball picked out Haller. The Ivory Coast international turned his marker and waited for Adan to commit himself before placing the ball into the corner of the goal.
Ridle Baku replaces Kevin Mbabu in Wolfsburg's third change of the game.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!! PULISIC FINISHES AN INCISIVE CHELSEA BREAK!!!!! 2-0!!!!!! The home side double their lead through Pulisic, who clips an effort over Jardim. Kante is the architect of the goal as he surges through the middle of the Lille midfield and then supplies an offload to Pulisic. The USA international takes the ball in stride and then holds his composure to find the bottom-right corner with a strike over the Lille keeper.
Mazraoui has been relatively quiet tonight, but that is some way to make an impact as he gets an assist thanks to a superb pass.
And Tsimikas is also taken off, with Robertson on for him.
Liverpool are making a double change here and it's the goal scorer, Thiago, who goes off for Henderson.
Casemiro is booked after a strong challenge on Maycon in midfield.
Kante makes a charge through the Lille midfield and picks out the run of Pulisic to allow the forward to finish from close range.
Origi went down off the ball in the centre circle, and after receiving some treatment, he's going straight off to be replaced by Mane.
Capoue over-stretches after losing control of the ball. He catches Fabinho and goes into the book.
Jereme Roussillon replaces Paulo Otavio in Wolfsburg's second change of the game.
Taarabt is the first Benfica man to enter the book, tripping Keita as the Liverpool midfielder looks to accelerate through midfield.
The Lille players surrounded the referee to appeal for that red card and Ikone is shown a yellow card for his complaints
Costanza makes a poor challenge and he is now booked as a result.
Sanusi is replaced by Wendell in defence.
Inzaghi freshens up his midfield, with playmaker Perisic on in place of Dimarco.
Bayern have responded by making a double change of their own, with Coman heading off and he has been replaced by Musiala.
Pizzi is the third Benfica man to come off, with Rafa Silva coming on.
Yaremchuk is another to head off and he has been replaced by Nunez.
Benfica are making a triple substitution now, with Everton one of those coming off and he has been replaced by Goncalves.
Verbic is replaced by De Pena in attack.
Lukaku is also coming on for the hosts, replacing the underwhelming Pulisic in the Chelsea frontline.
Final roll of the dice for Atletico now as Kondogbia is taken off and replaced by Lemar.
Lemar is withdrawn after an uneventful game and is replaced by Correa.
Nacho, meanwhile, is finally replacing the injured Militao in the heart of the visitors' backline.
Hermoso leaves the field for the hosts and is replaced by Lodi.
Loftus-Cheek replaces Jorginho in the Chelsea midfield, as Tuchel looks to add some energy to the hosts' engine room.
Cole Palmer is also introduced by Pep Guardiola, in place of midfield talisman De Bruyne.
Salah's evening is done after adding another goal to his tally for the season. Keita replaces the forward.
Pioli withdraws Kalulu down the right flank as Florenzi enters the action.
Mane is withdrawn by Klopp after a solid shift. Gomez replaces the forward to shore up the defence.
Villarreal make the game's first change. Coquelin comes on for the quiet Trigueros.
Foden, who has been playing excellently tonight, is replaced by Raheem Sterling for City.
Torres comes off for Gomez.
Moriba looks to break away with his first touch but is pulled back by Hakimi. The PSG right-back is booked for this.
There's a double change for Porto here as well. Oliveira is the first to make way, with Vitinha on in his place.
And Conceicao is also being brought on in place of Taremi.
Montiel replaces the injured Navas for Sevilla.
Alan Patrick enters the action to replace Antonio in the middle of the park.

RED CARD FOR BARELLA! The Inter man receives his marching orders for punching Militao in the thigh as he gets up from the turf. It seems harsh but by the letter of the law, the referee's right to dismiss him.
Militao receives a yellow card for his barge on Barella. It was unnecessarily forceful.
Varane picks up a yellow card for wasting time before taking the free-kick.
Shaw tugs back Zappacosta to stop his driving run and is shown a yellow card.
Moreno gets cited now with a booking, leaving the talismanic star having to watch his step for the rest of this match.
Barkley, who played a big part in that equaliser, also comes off to be replaced by Hakim Ziyech.
Carvajal brings down De Bruyne with a loose challenge and goes into the book.
Rafa Mir replaces Rakitic now for Sevilla.
Tonali makes way from the Milan midfield and is replaced by Bakayoko.
Messias enters the action to replace Krunic in the final third for the visitors.
Florenzi comes on at the back for Milan to replace Kalulu at right-back.
Rakitskiy is withdrawn too for Zenit, and on comes Danil Krugovoy.
Off comes the booked Hudson-Odoi in Chelsea's first change, and he's replaced by Christian Pulisic.

GOOOALLLL!!!! Salzburg are back in front!!! It's Okafor who capitalises on a scramble in the Wolfsburg box, reacting quicker than any of the defenders to squeeze the ball past Casteels! He makes it 2-1 to Salzburg, and Okafor really deserves that goal, he's been excellent in this match.
Substitution Jesus Navas Gonzalez Gonzalo Ariel Montiel
A disappointing day for Diaz comes to an early end, as Jota comes on for Liverpool up front.
