RONALDO SCORES! Fernandes' corner is cleared, but United keep it alive and Shaw swings a brilliant cross in from the left. Ronaldo is hovering in the middle and gets in front of Palomino to get on the end of it. He thumps his header past Musso from close range to put United ahead. 3-2 United!
Pjanic is brought off for Ucan.
Vinicius gets to head off early with Madrid's victory now surely in the bag. Hazard gets a runout for Madrid.
Hakimi scythes down Vinicius with a loose challenge and goes into the book.
Kobel guessed the right way and managed to prevent the spot-kick from going in as he flung himself to his left.
Goncalves misses the chance to score his hat-trick, seeing his tame penalty into the bottom-right corner kept out!
Fernando is also making his way around the pitch as Mudryk gets the chance to impress.
Traore heads down the tunnel, assisted by two physios. The Moldovan midfielder Cojocaru comes on for Sheriff.

TWO FOR HAALAND! Dortmund go five up, as Dahoud swings in a corner from the left, and Haaland repeats the trick by leaping clear of a hapless Besiktas defence to head down into the net from 10 yards. Haaland is in search of a hat-trick, and it is now 5-0 to Die Schwarzgelben!
Dahoud curled a corner into the right area for Haaland to attack with a powerful downward header.
Juve aren't taking any chances with McKennie, so he limps his way off-field and Zakaria comes on to replace him.
Hutchinson comes on for Topal.
Inzaghi seems to be protecting his front two from injury, with Dzeko replaced by Correa.
The Inter boss also makes an offensive change, bringing Dimarco off for Perisic at left wing-back.
Inzaghi throws a fresh pair of legs on in midfield, replacing Vecino with Gagliardini for the closing stages.
Dumfries hauls Mudryk down by his shirt as the substitute scampered away from him in extremely cynical fashion and earns a deserved yellow card.
Diaz has put forward another tireless effort and is replaced by Origi in the final third.
Stones is arguing that City should have a penalty and the referee books him for dissent.
Final change for Sporting now, with Braganca going off for Essugo.
Fernandinho goes into the book for protesting to the referee about the decision.
Porto make four changes to try and refresh their side. The first sees Joao Mario make way for Oliveira.
Grujic comes off in the fourth change with Corona taking his place.
Bruno's dribble through the middle is stopped unfairly by Jovic. A yellow card is the Serbian's reward.
Alexander-Arnold looks a tad disappointed as he is withdrawn for Gomez for the final nine minutes.
The injured Montero is off, and Uysal replaces him.

GOAL!!! PORRO CONVERTS THE REBOUND!!! Kobel's penalty save from Goncalves' tame effort bounces back into play and Porro is on it in an instant, nodding the loose ball across goal and inside the far post! It's 3-0 to Sporting!
Shaw touched the ball back to Pogba before moving into more space and he whipped a wonderful cross into the box when it came back to him.
Grealish gets the last 10 minutes off having scored a lovely goal. Jesus takes his place in City's front line.
Danjuma made the decisive impact tonight and is now withdrawn from the action for Chukwueze.
After an altercation with Aaronson before a free-kick, Ocampos is shown a yellow card.
Aurier replaces Foyth for the closing stages of the game on the right flank for Villarreal.
Corona gets the better of Kalulu down the right again and the defender is late with his tackle. He protests his innocence but is still shown a yellow card.
Zhegrova enters the action for Lille to replace David, who was not overly influential this evening.
Lednev makes his way onto the pitch to replace Lednev.
Nkunku heads off. His hat-trick looks like being in vain for Leipzig but he's certainly caught the eye. Gvardiol comes on for him.
Taarabt comes on for the closing stages to replace Joao Mario.
Darwin is withdrawn for the final nine minutes and is replaced by Ramos.
Ben Arfa replaces Sanches, who has had a difficult evening for the visitors.

GOAL! Firmino grabs his second and makes it 5-1! Jones fires a low shot at goal from the edge of the box, which is blocked by Cardoso and then falls straight to the feet of Firmino in front of goal. The striker then takes his time and slots it into the back of the net. The goal is initially ruled out for offside, but after a long VAR review, the decision is overturned and it stands as Firmino just managed to stay onside.
Lo Celso goes into the book for a foul on Fabinho.
Shaparenko is off for Shepelev,
Milan are making a double change as they try to see out this game. Bennacer is the first to make way, with Florenzi on in his place.
Young Boys wisely replace Martins before he receives a second yellow card. Rieder replaces him.
Simeone makes the surprising choice to withdraw Joao Felix. Cunha replaces the Portuguese. A bold move considering Joao Felix's recent form.
After an excellent display, Dybala is rested for the last 10 minutes, as Ramsey continues his return from injury with another cameo role.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!! BENZEMA CONVERTS FROM THE SPOT!!!!!! 4-3!!!!! Benzema notches his second of the night to bring Madrid back into the game yet again. The Frenchman goes for panenka chip right down the middle of the goal and finds the net as Ederson dives early to his left. A huge goal for Madrid and yet another for the veteran forward.
Stanisic is on for Bayern at the back to replace Sule for the closing stages.
Cuadrado is rested for the final few minutes, with Kulusevski given the chance to feature in his homeland.
Garmash catches Joao Mario late with a high challenge and he is booked after committing a few fouls.
Sabitzer comes on to shore up the Bayern midfield as he replaces Muller.
Emotions are running high here and now Delaney is booked for a reckless challenge.

BENFICA LEVEL! It is now 3-3 at Anfield, as Nunez powers a shot from the left side of the box into the bottom-right corner, following a throughball from Mario. Remarkably, it's 6-4 on aggregate in this wide open tie!
Valverde offers fresh legs in midfield as he replaces Modric for the final eight minutes.
Vinicius makes way for the visitors after earning a free-kick in a useful position. Hazard enters the action to replace the Brazilian.
Gavi goes into the book for a foul on Goretzka.
Ukrainian attacker Yaremchuk is the next man to enter the fray for the hosts, replacing Everton, who missed their best chance to level the score.
Nagelsmann turns to his bench for the first time as Gnabry replaces Musiala.
United are making their final change following the equaliser. Sancho goes off, with Lingard on for him.
Wendell is booked after tripping Correa near the touchline.
Coman replaces Sane in the final third for the visitors.
Amorim appears to be keeping it as tight as possible as defender Neto replaces Porro for the final seven minutes of normal time.
Lemar is withdrawn as Suarez enters the fold in the final third. Simeone is going for it with eight minutes left.
Zenit are making another change now as Kuzyaev making way for Kravtsov.
Making an impact from the bench, Mario plays an accurate ball in for Nunez to strike.
Otavio departs with Vieira coming on.
Saelemaekers is also being taken off, with Kalulu replacing him.
Mbabu makes his way onto the pitch in place of Vranckx.
Dybala adds to his excellent performance in this match with the unselfish assist, and after missing some great chances earlier in the match, Morata has a goal to savour at last.

GOOOALLL!!!! Morata finally has his goal!! Dybala profits from a loose ball and feeds his strike partner, and this time Morata makes no mistake in firing the shot first-time, underneath Kritsyuk to make it 4-1!! A three-goal lead, and surely three Group H points for Juve!
Yaremchuk makes way for Nunez up top.
Rafa also heads off with Goncalves taking his place.
Final roll of the dice for Milan here as Krunic is taken off and replaced by Maldini.
Richards just slips as he tries to dispossess Araujo and ends up standing on the defender's foot. He's shown a yellow card.
Souza has been overwhelmed in midfield, so may be glad to be substituted. Besiktas veteran Hutchinson is on for the final few minutes.
Porto throw on Martinez up top in place of Taremi.
Yakhshiboev has been quiet tonight for Sheriff and he is now replaced by Julien.
What a night for Brozovic as he now has one goal and one assist to his name after Sanchez's strike.

WHAT AN IMPACT - SHERIFF 0-3 INTER - Within 30 seconds of coming off the bench, Sanchez makes it three-nil as he scores his first goal of the season. That should be game set and match in Moldova, with Sanchez collecting Brozovic's pass before smashing his shot past Athanasiadis.

CITY DOWN TO 10! Silva is running down the left and he tries to shield the ball from Walker, who is coming in quickly behind him. The right-back seems to just kick out at the back of Silva and the referee shows him a straight red card.
Rekik is booked after bringing down Arnold in the middle of the pitch.
Paulinho, who won the penalty that has seemingly sealed Sporting's place in the Champions League knockout stages, is replaced by Tomas.
For arguing that Jordan should be booked for time-wasting, Arnold is instead shown a yellow card by the unimpressed referee.
Sevilla decide on a third change, and goalscorer Jordan is offered a rest, allowing Delaney to come on and shore up the midfield.
Clement now sends on Wesley, with De Ketelaere making his way to the bench.
Sowah has had a quiet night and he is now replaced by Izquierdo.
Wagner makes another pair of changes, with Moumi Ngamaleu replaced by Siebatcheu in attack as Young Boys push for an equaliser.
Allegri adds some pace into his midfield as Bernardeschi makes way for Cuadrado.
Final change for Liverpool now, with Oxlade-Chamberlain being replaced by Milner.
Sane latches on to a cross from Gnabry and gets the better of Otamendi with an element of fortune. He then offload to Lewandowski to complete the finish.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!! LEWANDOWSKI TAPS HOME!!!!! 3-0 BAYERN!! The German side surely secure the win this evening as the Pole converts an offload from Sane, tapping home into an empty net. Bayern open up Benfica down the right flank and Gnabry's cross finds its way into the feet of Sane. He turns past Otamendi with a slice of luck and then spots an unmarked Lewandowski at the back post. The forward makes no mistake with his finish.
Weah comes on for David.
Kravtsov replaces Sutormin for the closing stages of the contest for the hosts.
As Ajax's frustration grows, Timber is shown a yellow card for fouling the impressive Benfica captain, Otamendi, in an aerial challenge.
Goalscorer Silva is also withdrawn by Jesse Marsch, and Emil Forsberg comes on in his place.
Silva is also coming on to replace Azpilicueta.
Coman goes down looking for a foul and when he doesn't get it, he sticks out a leg to trip Wober. He's shown the first yellow card of the game.
Verratti is also withdrawn by Mauricio Pochettino, and Eric Ebimbe comes onto the pitch.
There'll be no hat-trick for Mbappe in this game, as the scorer of the first two goals, inside seven minutes, comes off for Mauro Icardi.
There's another Juve substitute incoming. Bernardeschi replaces Locatelli.
Fourth change for Milan now as Rebic goes off for Maldini.
Havertz is the latest Chelsea player to be rested with the weekend in mind, and Ziyech replaces him for the final few minutes.
Chiellini enters the action for the home side to shore up the defence.
Loftus-Cheek catches Bamba on the ankle with a lunge and goes into the book.
Bakayoko enters the action to replace Krunic in the Milan midfield.
Correa collects a yellow card after booting the ball at Grealish's face while he laid on the ground. Guardiola did his best to play peacemaker, and the pushing and shoving eventually came to a halt.
Dulanto cleans out Antonio and becomes the latest man to be booked in this contest.
Telles is the latest player to go into the referee's book after he clatters into Llorente with a late challenge.
Antony is the architect once again for Ajax with a dangerous cross from the right flank that Haller rises to head past Kobel.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!!!!! HALLER HEADS AJAX IN FRONT!!!! 2-1 AJAX!!!! The Dutch side take the lead through a sublime header from Haller. Antony again cuts inside from the right flank and delivers a precise cross with his left foot into the box. Haller rises ahead of Akanji and guides his effort away from Kobel into the left corner of the net. Dortmund's defence has been undone in the closing stages.
Simakan is subbed off, and he'll be glad to see the back of Mbappe as he's replaced by Yussuf Poulsen.
Cunha - who came on as a sub himself - is replaced by Lodi as Atletico look to tighten up.
Xeka is replaced by Mvom Onana in midfield.
The impressive Angelino is also replaced, by Benjamin Henrichs.
Kimpembe goes into the book for his part in the melee.
Rodrygo is also cautioned for squaring up to Kimpembe.
It's another pair of changes for Young Boys as Wagner replaces Hefti with Maceiras as his side chase the game.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!!!!!!! SALAH MAKES IT TWO!!!!!! 2-0 LIVERPOOL!!!! The visitors double their lead courtesy of a precise strike from Salah. Once again a cross proves to be Inter's downfall as Van Dijk nods Alexander-Arnold's delivery towards the penalty spot. Konate wisely leaves the loose ball for Salah to strike and the forward makes no mistake, placing his effort away from Handanovic into the bottom-right corner with the aid of a deflection.
There's a double change for Chelsea in defence here, with Alonso the first to go off. Chilwell comes on in his place for his first appearance of the season.
Pulisic enters the action for Werner in the final third. The German made a telling impact on the game to give Chelsea a chance.
The second alteration sees midfielder Aebischer go off, with Spielmann taking his place in the side.
The lively Berghuis is substituted off for Taylor.
Calhanoglu is now taken off by Inzaghi, who replaces him with Vecino.
The referee shows Ugarte a card as he brings down Gundogan inside the centre circle.
The hosts make a change in attack, as Jota is substituted and Diaz takes his place up front.

GOAAAALL - BAYERN 6-1 SALZBURG - Muller gets his second of the evening as he converts another pass from Sane. The duo worked themselves into a good position inside the Salzburg box before Muller curled his shot into the bottom corner, although he looked to have miskicked it.
Lukas Nmecha sees a yellow for a foul on Wober.
Great play from Sane yet again, who has had a solid night at the office!
Tiago Djalo replaces Mehmet Zeki Celik in Lille's third change of the game.

Feddal joins the likes of Palhinha, Timber and Alvarez in the referee's book after a sloppy challenge on the latter. Alvarez poked the ball away from the Sporting defender, and he did not take too kindly to that and produced a crunching challenge as a result.
Sterling replaces Jesus for the closing stages of the game.
Hefti also goes off. Young Boys' Serbian winger Sulejmani comes on.

GOAL! ROBIN GOSENS MIGHT HAVE SAVED A POINT FOR ATALANTA! 1-1! Is that the goal to deny Villarreal a winning return to the Champions League? The Serie A team poke one in at close range, after a cross bounces between the defence and attack around the box. Game on!
Bozdogan, who appeared to be struggling after a tackle from Palhinha, is replaced by Ozyakup after only coming on in the 61st minute.
Albiol is applauded off as he leaves the field on a stretcher, and Mandi comes on in his place.
Haller's work is done, as he is brought off and Daramy comes on.
With the game decided, Mazraoui is given a rest and Rensch is afforded an opportunity to impress.
Kimpembe throws the ball at Vinicius and gives him a body-check for good measure. The referee spots it and books the defender.
Talk about a moment of inspiration. As the visitors' most recent change, Miranchuk was in the right place at the right time with that touch.

GOAL!!!! WHAT A GOAL FROM HEFTI!!!! The right-back drifts into a central area and strokes a sublime strike into the top-left corner past a helpless Musso! He could well have won the game for his side! It's 3-2 to Young Boys now!
Aebischer claims the assist, but all the credit has to go to Hefti for his sensational shot into the top corner from range.
Rodrygo's game is over after a decent outing for Madrid. Asensio is his replacement.
GOOOOALLLL!!! If the home fans were happy with their goal, they're not smiling any more. Fernandinho sends MAhrez through one-on-one, and the Algerian makes no mistake to make it 5-1 to City!!!
Juventus make their fifth change now as Aaron Ramsey replaces Rodrigo Bentancur.
Malmo make another substitution. Moisander comes on. Berget heads off.
Diaz makes way for Pepe in attack.
Mata replaces Maguire for the closing stages. United have committed all of their substitutes now.
Douglas Santos has had a fine outing and is now withdrawn for Krugovoy.
Casemiro also goes off. Blanco will get to enjoy the last few minutes of this match.
Militao wipes out Grealish on the charge down the left flank and goes into the book.
A great ball from Fernandinho to set up Mahrez, who extends his Champions League tally to three!
Tomas joins Feddal in the book for dissent.
Another Champions League debut is made for City, as Luke Mbete replaces Laporte at centre-back.
Second change for Lille now and Weah is taking a slow walk off the pitch to try and run the clock down. Yazici is on for him.
Two more changes for Lille as they hunt a late equaliser. The first sees Gudmundsson swap out for Reinildo.
Mostovoy enters the action to replace Dzyuba in the final third.
Arnold is booked for Wolfsburg, having brought down Onguene.
Another change for Villarreal now as Dia comes on in place of Gomez.
David is replaced by Lihadji in attack.
Barella is withdrawn by Inzaghi and is replaced in the midfield by Vecino.
Palhinha has worked hard as ever, but now comes off for Braganca.
Fabinho is given a well-earned rest with Milner taking his place.
Stanisic makes a burst down the right flank and spots the run of Sane, who finishes with a fine strike.
Yusuf Yazici replaces Jonathan Ikone in Lille's fourth change of the game.
Kolovos departs with Cojocaru coming on following that knock.
Goalscorer Okafor laps up the applause from the Salzburg bench as he makes way for Adamu.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!! SANE HAS HIS SECOND, BAYERN HAVE FOUR!!!! 4-0!!!!! Bayern are rampant in the closing stages of the game as Sane steers home a left-footed strike from 12 yards. Stanisic makes a good run down the right flank and bursts into the box. He cuts a low ball back for Sane, who strikes the ball hard first time into the left corner of the net giving Vlachodimos no chance.
Danjuma's night is also over as Emery sends on Pedraza.
Emery follows suit as he sends on Chukwueze, with Coquelin the one to make way.
Adams is booked by the referee for a cynical foul on Messi.
Sarabia is replaced by Tomas in attack.

GOAL! HAT-TRICK FOR LEWANDOWSKI! The striker just manages to stay onside as a long ball comes over the top of the Benfica defence by Neuer and Lewandowski controls it and then chips it over the top of Vlachodimos. The keeper gets a touch on it, but can't stop it from heading in and it's 5-2!
Navas is booked for his reaction to the challenge too.
Capaldo drags Navas down as the latter looks to break and is booked as tempers flare again.
It's not very often that a keeper provides the assist for a goal, but Neuer did there, perfectly finding Lewandowski and the striker just manages to stay onside and coolly finish.
Porto are making another change now and it's Martinez that's coming on for Taremi.
Roussillon makes way for Gerhardt in defence.
Lodi just peels away from Calabria on the far side of the box and cushions his header down into the middle for Griezmann.

GRIEZMANN EQUALISES! Atletico have been pushing and they've finally found an equaliser! Lodi heads it back across the box and nobody is picking up the Frenchman in the middle. He hits it on the half-volley and Maignan is left stranded as it nestles into the bottom corner for Griezmann's first goal since returning to the club. 1-1!
Liverpool are making a double change now as well with Salah the first to make way for Oxlade-Chamberlain.
And Henderson also goes off to a standing ovation from the crowd as he hands the armband onto his replacement, Milner.
Porro is substituted for Sporting, giving Tabata a few minutes to make a major impact.
Reis is withdrawn with only a handful of minutes remaining: Esgaio comes on.
Otavio also comes off at the same time as Taremi and Martinez is the man to take his place.
Perisic also heads off to be replaced by Kolarov.
Two more changes for Inter. First of all, Brozovic is taken off for Sensi.
Balanta, who has just returned from suspension, finds himself in the book after a stupid challenge on the touchline.
Xeka is now on for Lille, as David comes off five minutes early.
More changes for Inter as Ranocchia steps into defence in place of De Vrij.
Hernandez is withdrawn for the closing stages and is replaced by Richards.
Apparently stricken by cramp, Valverde is taken off by Ancelotti, and Camavinga is his replacement in Madrid's midfield.
Ramirez replaces Buyalskyi for the visitors to boost their firepower for the closing stages.
Karavaev enters the game to replace Tsygankov in the final third.
For a late tackle on Salah, Bastoni becomes the latest name taken by the referee.

GOAL! MANCHESTER CITY 6-3 RB LEIPZIG! Jesus gets in on the act for City, smashing the ball into the top left corner as Leipzig fail to clear a corner and Mahrez's shot from outside the box. Gulacsi had made a decent stop from Mahrez to concede the corner. VAR checks the goal for offside against Dias who'd touched the ball in the build-up, but the goal stands.
Torres inflicts a late challenge on Mane and is rightly shown a yellow card.
Another Benfica change now, with Joao Mario the man coming off and he has been replaced by Taarabt.
Rodri took out Cunha in the build-up to the Suarez chance and is retrospectively booked by the referee.
Bonucci's eventful performance ends, as he's replaced by Daniele Rugani.
Leao reluctantly makes his way off the pitch as Pioli throws on Maldini in search of a winner.

GOAL! JUVENTUS 0-2 VILLARREAL (1-3 ON AGGREGATE)! Villarreal are surely heading to the Champions League quarter-finals! Torres stabs the corner into the net with a side-foot finish as Aurier flicks it into the centre. Juve's marking for the goal is dire.

Aurier made enough of a nuisance of himself in the box to get his head to the corner, and Torres was in the right place in the centre to finish it off. Juve are staring down the barrel of yet another round-of-16 defeat in the Champions League.
Salah lifted in a cross from the right and Jota tried to go for goal with a high volley. He catches Trippier in the face and is shown a yellow card for the high boot.
Kouassi's injury is too severe for him to continue, and Malik Tillman comes on in his place.
PSG finally make some changes and the first sees Di Maria replaced by Draxler.
Bayern make a late change now, with Gnabry replaced by Sarr.
Dybala is given a massive ovation by the home fans as he comes off, and Dejan Kulusevski replaces him.
Alexander-Arnold makes way for the visitors and is replaced at right-back by Gomez.
And Seiwald is also making way, with Bernardo on in his place.
Salzburg are making a double change as they look for a late equaliser. Aaronson is first to go off, with Kjaergaard on for him.
Leipzig also make a change, with Laimer replaced by Henrichs.
A silly challenge from Jesus sees him pick up a yellow card, and he is now suspended for the second leg.
Lacroix is shown a yellow card for timewasting as Wolfsburg continue to keep Lille at bay.
Weghorst is booked for his protests about the penalty incident.
Mahrez has made the decisive impact tonight to put City on the brink of the Champions League with a brilliant strike. He is replaced by Fernandinho to shore up the City midfield.
There will be no hat-trick for Wijnaldum as he heads off and is replaced by Herrera.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!! LEWANDOWSKI SCORES HIS SECOND WITH A CLOSE-RANGE BLAST!!!!! 3-0 BAYERN!!!! Lewandowski pounces on another rebound to fire home a third Bayern goal after Gnabry strikes the post. He holds his composure after Gnabry's blast from six yards rattles the woodwork. Lewandowski rounds a challenge from Pique before hammering an effort on his left foot past Ter Stegen into the back of the net. Clinical from the Pole.
Bernardo also makes way and is booed off the field, with Delap the one to replace him.
Guardiola continues to protect his first-team stars, as Ake replaces Laporte.
That first touch from Pulisic to beat Barrios was fantastic play from the substitute, and after playing in Werner, gets the assist after the Germany striker's clinical finish!
Taarabt's night is over as he is replaced by Bernardo.

GOOOALLLLL!!!! It's lovely play from Chelsea, and Pulisic plays in Werner inside the box. He's crowded, but he cuts inside Karavaev and smashes a low shot straight past Kerzhakov and into the back of the net, and it's 3-2!!! What a game!!
Nikolov replaces Castanedo for the home side to shore up the midfield.
Radeljic comes on to the field for the closing stages to replace the tiring legs of Addo.
De Zerbi throws Marlos on for Patrick in midfield, still searching for a winner as the final whistle approaches.
Haller is booked after clattering into Meras.
Lewandowski has already proven he can do it all tonight, but he gets an assist with just minutes remaining!

GOAAALLLL - BAYERN 7-1 SALZBURG - Now that is deserved. Sane gets a goal to add to his two assists, and Nagelsmann's side are taking Salzburg apart at will. Lewandowski managed to pick up possession on the edge of the Salzburg penalty box, and rather than shoot, he waited for Sane to overlap him. The visitors' defence fell for it, and before they could realise, Sane had smashed the ball into the roof of the net.
Danjuma is replaced Alcacer for the closing stages of the game in the final third.
Benzema is the first to make way, getting a brilliant reception from the visiting fans after his incredible display. Wales star Bale is on in his place.
Ceballos is also on for Valverde, who looked in some discomfort after that collision.
Sydorchuk goes off with Andrievskyi replacing him in midfield.
Brorsson pulls back Malcom on the charge and goes into the book.
Sensi gets less than five minutes to catch the eye, with Calhanoglu the one to make way.
Nunez heads off to great applause. Ramos takes his place for the last few minutes.
Substitution Jonathan Christian David Miguel Angelo da Silva Rocha
Substitution Jonathan Christian David Miguel Angelo da Silva Rocha
Rose brings Haaland off with just a few minutes or normal time left to play as Knauff comes on to replace him.
Taremi, who has disappointed for Porto here, is brought off by Sergio Conceicao and Pepe - not the former Real Madrid man - replaces him.
After grabbing an assist tonight, Perisic's night is now over, as Dimarco enters the game.
Fernando has done his bit for Shakhtar, scoring their only goal but he is now replaced by Dentinho.
Benfica get the party started, making a few changes to wind down the clock. Pizzi replaces Rafa.
Rakip, who's been busy in midfield for Malmo, also heads off. Birmancevic is his replacement.
Malmo's right wing-back Berget gets the last few minutes off. Larsson comes on for him.
Final change for Barcelona now and Xavi is bringing on Demir for the last few minutes in place of Gavi.
Oleksiy Shevchenko replaces Andriy Pyatov in Shakhtar Donetsk's fifth change of the game, with the goalkeeper coming on for some very rare minutes.
Gonzalez slides in on Joao Mario to become the latest Barca player to get booked. Barca are being humbled here.
Thiago has been industrious this evening and now makes way for Milner in the Liverpool midfield.
Barca bring some fresh faces on. Dest, who's back from injury, replaces Lenglet.
Araujo heads off too. Garcia replaces him at the back for Barca.
Tolisso enters the action in the Bayern midfield to replace Sabitzer.
Final change for Leipzig now and Moriba is on to replace Silva.
Juve have to go for broke now. Kean replaces the muted Morata up front.
Sazlburg captain Ulmer is brought off by Matthias Jiassle, and is replaced by Daouda Guindo.
Balanta's challenge enraged the visitors, and Wesley is booked for his part in the melee.

He was such a threat in that first half and De Sciglio has got his just reward with that touch. Spare a though for Zenit, very much as big a part of this match in drive and aplomb - but unless they can change something fast, the Juve man's well-lofted delivery is going to be the hilt of the knife against them.
Moriba was also booked for his part in the argument, and hopefully, the referee has control of matters now.

GOAL! DEJAN KULUSEVSKI FOR JUVENTUS IN THE FINAL ACT! 1-0! Zenit's hearts are broken but the Bianconeri will not care! They tip an average set-piece wide to the left flank to find Mattia De Sciglio, who controls his collection and floats it back in - whereupon the substitute glides a fantastic header from the middle to come in off the right edge.
Villarreal make a late change of their own to help them see this win out. Pedraza replaces Parejo.
Coman comes off the field after a fine performance and is replaced by Musiala.
Cards galore at the minute as Martinez is booked for a poor challenge.
Gasperini throws a striker in Muriel on for a wing-back in Maehle as he looks to salvage something from the game in the time that remains.
Gonzalo Montiel replaces Navas in Sevilla's latest change.
Former West Ham man Mario replaces Ramos as Benfica's number 10 as the hosts look for a route back to parity.
Eile makes his way on to the field to replace Brorsson for the visitors.

GOAAAAALLLL! IT'S GAME OVER AS LIVERPOOL GET A THIRD! Former Porto man Diaz has surely put this game beyond his old Portuguese rivals, racing onto a brilliant ball from Keita before rounding the keeper and rolling the ball home from a tight angle. A huge goal for the Reds!
Another change for Bayern as Davies comes on for the final few minutes, with Hernandez the one to make way.
Brugge substitution. De Ketelaere, who faded after a promising hour or so, makes way for Sowah.
Final change for Juventus now, and it's De Sciglio that's making way for Pellegrini.
Substitution Alberto Moreno Perez Alfonso Pedraza Sag
Pavard picked out his teammate perfectly at the far post and Choupo-Moting just had to make the contact and send it towards goal, which he makes no mistakes with.

GOAL! It's five! Choupo-Moting gets amongst the goals now after only being on the pitch for a few minutes! Bayern kept up the pressure in the final third and the ball came out to Pavard down the right wing, who whips a cross into the box, which is met by the head of Choupo-Moting, who powers it into the back of the net.
There's also a double change for City. Palmer is on in place of De Bruyne.
Third change for Salzburg now, with Adeyemi going off for Kjaergaard.
Ibrahimovic tries to bring it down but catches Mbemba in the face with a very high boot. He's claiming he made contact with the ball, but he's booked.
Ben Arfa pulls back Werner on the charge down the right flank and goes into the book.
And Ake, who was moving gingerly after a heavy landing on his back, is taken off, with Dias on for him.
Maier enters the action to replace Elia for the closing stages of the game.
Kohn is dawdling over a goal-kick in an attempt to run the clock down, and he's booked for time-wasting.
Dalot pulls back Lodi on the charge and goes into the book.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!! MESSIAS STUNS THE WANDA METROPOLITANO!!!!!! 1-0 MILAN!!!! The Italian side take the lead in the dying stages of the game as Messias rises to plant a bullet header past Oblak from six yards. Kessie does brilliantly down the left flank to raid at the Atletico defence before supplying a perfect left-footed cross. Messias gets between Savic and Gimenez before applying the finish.
Gagliardini replaces Vidal in the Inter midfield for the closing stages of the contest.
Kessie makes a fine run down the left flank before delivering a precise cross for Messias to score.
Adeyemi has been impressive once again, and is brought off for Chukwubuike Adamu.
Okafor, arguably tonight's man-of-the-match, is replaced by youngster Roko Simic.
Rulli is booked by the referee for timewasting. You can't blame the Villarreal keeper at this stage, he's been the busiest of any of his teammates by far in the second stanza.
Lamela is booked for tripping Ikone as Lille countered.
Benzema has barely had a touch tonight and is withdrawn for Bale in the final third.
Gueye comes on in place of Danilo, who was booked earlier in the contest. Pochettino is not taking any risks here.
Goalscorer Fati makes way for Balde.
And Van de Beek is also getting a rare chance to come on as he replaces Fernandes.
event_player: [' D. van de Beek ', ' Bruno Fernandes ']

comment: Double change for United as they try to find a late equaliser. McTominay is the first to make way, with Sancho on in his place.
Vallejo comes on to replace Militao.
Ulmer goes in the book after catching Mbabu as he turned away from him.
De Ligt jogs off for Rugani to get a brief run-out, as the clock ticks down towards the final whistle.
Yellow Card Benjamin Andre
Roussillon concedes a messy, avoidable challenge right on the lip of his own box and gets booked for it.
Julian Nagelsmann also brings off Sane for Omar Richards, thus every outfield Bayern substitute is on the pitch.
For an obvious foul on Munir, a yellow card is doled out to Andre.
Dumfries makes way for Darmian at right wing-back for the home side.
Ranocchia comes on for the closing stages for De Vrij, who must be carrying a knock.
And Rakitic converts to make it 1-1 from the penalty spot! He sends the keeper Casteels the wrong way and hammers it into the bottom left to level for his side.
Balanta is booked after a slide tackle on Forsberg. He could've gone in the book three or four times over in this game.
Yellow Card Benjamin Andre

Anthony has lost his cool, and after squaring up to Nunez, he has dipped his head into the Benfica striker. Even though the frontman made the most of it, Anthony should be off the pitch, but somehow he has only picked up a yellow card!
Brandt has been virtually invisible in his midfield role, and is replaced by Knauff for the final few minutes.
Capaldo is booked for Salzburg, meaning that he'll miss the next match.
Moreno deserves heaps of praise for his pass, putting the ball on a plate for Chukwueze.

GOOOALLL!!! That might just do it! Villarreal break at lightning speed through Alberto Moreno, he unselfishly feeds Gerard Moreno, who's shot is saved by Von Ballmoos before the substitute follows in to make it 3-1, and surely now, put this game to bed for Villarreal!
Andre goes in the book for clattering Delaney outside the box. This free-kick is in a dangerous position too.

GOAAAALLLL!!!!!!!! BAYERN 1-1 VILLARREAL - THEY HAVE DONE IT, Villarreal have scored at the death, and they are minutes away from eliminating Bayern. Parejo's quick thinking in the middle of the park was vital, as he played a crucial pass to Lo Celso before Moreno was picked out. The Villarreal striker looked across the pitch, and Chukwueze was waiting at the far post. The sub didn't make a clean connection with the ball, but it was enough to beat Neuer.
Discipline has gone out of the window in the final stages of an otherwise fairly contested encounter, and Ocampos is the latest man to take a booking for a foul on Djalo inside the Lille area.
Milner refuses to back away as Costa waits to take a free-kick for Porto. He's booked for it, and that means he'll miss Liverpool's final group game against Milan.
Wendel comes off for Zenit, and Daniil Kuznetsov takes his place.
Late Liverpool change now, with Jota coming off and he has been replaced by Origi.
Cojocaru is booked following a cynical trip on Sanchez.
Mario Gaspar replaces Pedraza in Villarreal's final change.
Nacho is replaced by Vazquez after struggling with an apparent injury.
Asensio replaces Vinicius for the closing stages of the game.
Fred has gone down holding his hamstring, and he's taken straight off by the medical team. Matic is on in his place.
Zenit make their fourth change now as Daniil Krugovoy replaces Dmitriy Chistyakov.
Substitution Arnaut Danjuma Adam Groeneveld Boulaye Dia

GOAL!!!! WHAT AN INTRODUCTION FROM MURIEL!!! Just one minute after coming on, the striker steps up to a free-kick at a sharp angle to the left of goal, but his strike takes a slight deflection and sneaks inside the bottom corner of the near post! Atalanta are level again and it's 3-3!
And Krugovoy is also being brought on for Rakitskiy.
Goncalves will rue his failure to seal his hat-trick from the spot, but has had a terrific game and goes off for Nazinho.
Birmancevic is withdrawn by Tomasson for the closing stages as Nalic replaces the forward.
Vazquez brings down Mbappe with a cynical challenge and goes into the book. Madrid are admitting here that they cannot stop Mbappe without fouling him.
Draxler enters the action for Hakimi for the closing stages of the game.
There's another double change for Zenit here. Mostovoy is coming on in place of Claudinho.
Now it's Wagner's turn to make a positive change, replacing midfielder Martins Pereira with a forward in Kanga.
Amorim makes two more changes, bringing goalscorer Porro off for Ribeiro in the first.
Larin goes in the book for a poor challenge on Klaassen.
A final change for Wolfsburg sees Brooks brought off for Ginczek to feature in the closing moments of the game.
Camavinga makes a well-timed run to break into the left-inside channel before directing a pass towards Rodrygo to convert.
Neto receives a yellow card for a late challenge inside his own half.
Zappacosta slides in clumsily on Maceiras and is shown a deserved yellow card. That was a poor challenge.
United substitution. Martial is on for Fred.
Bamba is booked for dissent after a foul from Ikone.
Kulusevski is booked almost straight away, for a foul on Erokhin.
Iqbal makes his United bow as he replaces Lingard.
Starting centre-back Neto has been withdrawn after getting a cramp, and Zouhair Feddal will see out the game in his place.
Greenwood is also being taken off, with Lingard on for him.
Barca make a substitution to shore up their defence following Garcia's dismissal. Mingueza replaces Roberto.
Opening goalscorer Pino comes off, and the birthday boy is replaced by Moises Gomez.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!! RODRYGO SCORES AT THE DEATH!!!!!!! 1-0 MADRID!!! The visitors take the lead through Rodrgyo as he converts a cutback from Camavinga into the back of the net. Camavinga makes a great run into the final third in the left-inside channel and he directs a low ball into the middle. Rodrygo gets ahead of Bastoni and directs a left-footed effort on the volley away from Handanovic into the bottom-right corner.
Slimani comes off in Sporting's latest change, ands he's replaced by Rodrigo Duarte Ribeiro.
Capoue worked hard after losing the ball on the touchline and was rewarded for his pressing as he won the ball in a very dangerous area and allowed Danjuma the chance to tuck home.
With the end of the game in sight, Ghezzal is replaced by Tore on the right wing.
Cuadrado goes into the book for time-wasting.

GOAL! RENATO STEFFEN GIVES WOLFSBURG SOMETHING TO CHEER! 3-1! It is scant consolation now, as Lille fail to clear the edge of their box cleanly, but the finish, curved back in towards the right post, is a lovely one all the same.

GOAL! REAL MADRID 1-2 SHERIFF! What an incredible goal by Thill! The Luxembourgish midfielder receives a flicked pass from Traore and smashes a left-footed half-volley towards goal from outside the box. It sails past Courtois to find the top left corner! What a historic victory this could turn out to be if Sheriff can just hold on!
It was a great run from Pote and he managed to nudge it to Paulinho just before Vida's tackle, and the striker did the rest with a brilliant strike!

Paulinho wraps it up! 4-1! The visitors hit Besiktas on the break again, but this time they capitalise. Pote runs towards the defence, before Vida's challenge sends the ball to Paulinho. The striker takes a touch, before bending a delightful, 25-yard strike into the far top corner!
Yellow Card Lucas Ariel Ocampos
Yellow Card Lucas Ariel Ocampos
Gomez is on for Alexander-Arnold for Liverpool, as Klopp looks to see out the dying moments of this game.
Meanwhile, the experienced Milner replaces Keita, who contributed enormously to the third goal with his superb ball to Diaz.
Yellow Card Luis Fernando Muriel Fruto
Savage also makes his debut for the Red Devils as he replaces Mata.
In the scrappy build of that encounter, Arnold looked to get the penultimate touch. He is handed an assist for that.
Innocent has struggled with an injury in the last few minutes, with Nalic now on in his place.

GOAL!!! DANJUMA MAKES IT 2-0 TO VILLARREAL!!! That goal has surely secured a win for the hosts! Capoue nicks the ball back on the edge of the box after losing it and Danjuma races into the area and slots inside the near post!
Another double change for United here, and it looks like Telles was just struggling with an injury, so Fred is on to replace him.
Camara comes off for Kjeargaard.
Zenit make their fifth change now as Aleksandr Erokhin replaces Claudinho, moments before Chiesa shades a finish to the left of the goal.
Gasperini makes two late changes now as he looks to see the game out. Zappacosta goes off and is replaced by on-loan left-back Pezzella.
Verissimo freshens up his attack, with Nunez replaced by Lazaro.
Traore is replaced by Cojocari up top.
Rieks is shown a yellow card after protesting the penalty decision.
Larsson is booked for the foul that resulted in the penalty.
Pereira replaces Gueye for the closing stages of the game. Gueye has been outstanding today.
Here is the enforced Benfica change, with Rafa replaced by Pizzi for the final few minutes.
It's a late, needless challenge from Kjaergaard as he slides in on Fonte and it earns him a yellow card.
Juventus goalscorer Kean makes way for Da Graca.
Nmecha needlessly picks up a booking for handball; ruling him out of the final group game due to suspension.
Rabiot is the latest player to be booked for a poorly-timed challenge.
Allegri makes another change in midfield as Bentancur is replaced by Miretti.
Gasperini's second change is in midfield, where Freuler goes off for fellow new signing Koopmeiners.
Dest goes into the book for a challenge on Vitinho.
Choupo-Moting is thrown on by Nagelsmann and he replaces Muller.
Substitution Joakim Maehle Pedersen Davide Zappacosta
De Ligt is booked for his handball. Danjuma will be the player to take Villarreal's second penalty of the game.
Villarreal are making another double change now. Danjuma goes off, with Dia coming on in his place.
Thill is shown a yellow card for ripping his shirt off in celebration. Who wouldn't if they scored a goal like that against Madrid of all teams?

SANCHO SCORES! And that will do it for United! Fred does well to win the ball back again in his own half, and he sets United on the counter. Fernandes touches it into Sancho on the right of the box. The defenders are slow to get out to him, and he fires his shot past Rulli and into the roof of the net for his first United goal. 2-0 United!
Draxler is withdrawn for defender Thilo Kehrer; a clear sign than PSG coach Mauricio Pochettino wants to hold onto this slim lead.
And Chukwueze is the other player taken off, with Pino on for him.
Paredes brings down Kroos to stop a Madrid counter and goes into the book.
Felix is withdrawn after a good performance. Felipe comes on to shore up the Atletico defence.
Rashford makes a great run down the left to get United upfield before squaring it to Fernandes, who just touched it through to Sancho.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!!!!! RODRYGO GETS A GOAL BACK!!!!!! 1-1!!!!! Madrid have a glimmer of hope as Rodrygo converts at the near post. Benzema steers a cross from Camavinga towards the middle and Rodrygo reacts ahead of Ederson to fire home.
Solet was preoccupied with making sure Lewandowski didn't get to the ball and Muller just edged in front of him to flick it on.

GOALLL! CORREA! 2-0. Atletico wrap the game up. Correa hits Porto on the counter and is clean through on goal with 40 yards to run! The attacker gets all the way into the box, before driving a composed finish beyond Costa!
Felix Mambimbi comes on for Young Boys, in place of Fassnacht, who has impressed in this game.
It was Griezmann's pass that released Correa, but that was all about the attacker keeping cool and finishing past Costa.
Modric makes way as the final heads towards stoppage time, and Ceballos is his midfield replacement.
Benzema steers a cross from Camavinga towards the near post for Rodrygo to score.
Danjuma has been a stand-out for Villarreal, and is replaced by Samuel Chukwueze.
Madrid could have defended Traore's pass better but take nothing away from Thill's strike. That flew clean and true into the net. He'll remember that goal forever.

COMAN EQUALISES! Salzburg's defenders just switch off for a moment as Pavard lifts a long ball over the top from the right. Muller manages to glance it on in the middle and Coman is running onto it at the far post and finally gets his reward as he pokes it past Kohn from close range. 1-1!
Leao is late as he tries to nick the ball off Otavio and he stands on the winger's foot. He's the latest player to have his name taken by the referee.
It's good work from Greenwood on the edge of the box to keep the attack alive for United and hold of the defenders before picking out Ronaldo.

RONALDO EQUALISES AGAIN! Ronaldo cuts inside from the left, but Zapata slides in to win it off him. Greenwood keeps it alive on the edge of the area by lifting it over two defenders with two good touches before he picks out Ronaldo. He takes the shot on the volley, firing a powerful, low shot past Musso. There's a VAR check for a possible handball against Greenwood, but the goal stands. It's 2-2!
Ake squared up to Savic and is booked by the referee.
Savic goes into the book for his part in the melee. The defender may have been lucky to remain on the field.
Carvajal delivers a precise cross from the right flank that Asensio flicks to Rodrygo, who guides the ball away from Ederson into the net.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!! RODRYGO LEVELS THE TIE!!!!!!!!! 2-1 ON THE NIGHT!!!! Out of nowhere Madrid are back in the game as Rodrygo dispatches a perfect header past Ederson. Carvajal delivers a precise cross from the right flank that Asensio flicks on, allowing the Brazilian to rise between Laporte and Dias to place his effort into the top-left corner. What a turnaround at the Bernabeu.
Third change for United now and it's Ronaldo that's going off for Matic.
Gilberto is the next man to make way for Benfica, as Dias comes on.
Everton is replaced by Almeida for the closing stages.
After bagging a brace to help his side into the semis, Firmino is brought off; Origi comes on to typically warm applause.

And there is Benzema's goal! After a brilliant performance that was only missing a goal, the French striker finally gets his name on the scoresheet as he sidefoots an Asensio cross into the back of the net to make it 5-0 to the visitors.
Hernandez is booked late on for tripping up Karavaev as he broke forward on the counter.
As usual, Thill has been Sheriff's most creative player, and he gets his reward with an assist in stoppage time.

GOAAAALLL - SHERIFF 1-3 INTER - The visitors lose their clean sheet at the death as Traore heads into the far corner to give the home fans something to smile about. Thill's curling ball in was superb, and Traore climbed high at the near post to head past Handanovic.
It was a superb delivery by Asensio to find Benzema in the box for him to finish.
Pena clattered into the back of Matic after he played a pass and he's shown a yellow card.
Vinicius is withdrawn for the dying seconds of the game and is replaced Asensio.
Dimarco enters the action for the dying minutes to replace Bastoni at the back.
Donnarumma is booked for dissent after protesting the penalty decision with the referee.
Having just picked up a knock, Gilberto is taken off; Lazaro comes on to help Benfica see out stoppage time.
Camavinga takes one for the team by fouling Pulisic preventing him from finding Havertz on a counter following a mistake by Carvajal.
Ramos has put in a willing shift, but is now replaced by Bernardo for the final few moments.
Adams trips Grealish to stop his run down the left, and he's shown a yellow card.
Gilberto is unable to continue through injury, with Goncalves his replacement.
Sporting make three changes to slow the game down. The first sees Feddal make way for Neto.
Lo Celso is shown a yellow card, but he will not care as he tries to waste more time.
Final change for Porto now as Grujic comes on in place of Otavio.
Sheriff substitution. Nikolov replaces Kolovos in midfield.
Zapata catches Aebischer in the side of the head by accident as he tries to hold off the midfielder's challenge. The Atalanta striker is booked as a result.
Mazraoui was a real threat for Ajax tonight, but his night is over, with Rensch on in his place!
Francisco Conceicao is shown a late yellow card for fouling Kessie and then kicking the ball away to waste time.
Vlachodimos is shown the yellow card for taking too long over the goal-kick. Barca fans had been baying for it for a while.
Camara blocks the pass into the box and Sabitzer clatters into him in an attempt to win it back, which earns him a yellow card.
Braganca comes on in place of Matheus.
Pote makes way for Santos after a lively display.

And De Paul makes it 3-0! De Paul shrugs off Mbemba on the counter and advances into the box before hitting a shot against Costa from close range. The rebound falls to Griezmann whose effort is blocked away by Pepe, but De Paul is there to nudge it over the line from two yards!

GOOOALLL!!! IT'S FOUR!!! Gerard Moreno finds himself in space on the edge of the box, and looks for the substitute Chukwueze who, with his first touch, dispatches the ball home to make it 4-1 and seal the game in Villarreal's favour! Young Boys have fought gallantly, but the away side are turning the screw now as we enter the last minutes.
Cancelo grabs his third assist of the game and his pass for Jesus was probably the easiest. He has run the show for City. And that's it!
Elia also leaves the pitch. Kanga, another forward, comes on.

GOAL! MANCHESTER CITY 4-1 CLUB BRUGGE! City are running away with the three points now. Cancelo does well to find Jesus to the left of the box and the Brazilian caps an assured City performance by opening his body up and slotting into the far bottom corner.
Moreno has been his industrious but effective self in this match, and adds an assists to his tally, which of course already includes the second goal.
Weghorst comes off for Gerhardt after being booked.
Here are those Young Boys changes. Lauper off. Zesiger on.
Vrsaljko's clumsy challenge ensures he collects a yellow card.

GOAL! JUVENTUS 0-3 VILLARREAL (1-4 ON AGGREGATE!) Juventus have totally unravelled here. Danjuma confidently slots his penalty into the bottom left corner of the net. This has become one of Villarreal's greatest European performances.
Matip gets a toe to the ball but he takes out Cunha, who is running through into the box. Matip is shown a yellow card for it, and he clearly isn't happy that the foul's gone against him.

GOAL! IT'S 2-2! Szoboszlai steps up to take the penalty and he fires the ball into the bottom left corner of the net! It was just out of the reach of Donnarumma, who dived the right way and the keeper is furious that he didn't manage to save that, but it just had too much pace on it.
GOOOALLL!!! Zenit have another! Surely just a consolation, but it's a really well taken goal by Azmoun who takes Dzyuba's pass well and instinctively slots the ball past Szczesny to make it 4-2!
Ederson is also shown a yellow card for dissent.
Salah makes way after another productive performance. Williams replaces him for the closing stages.
Late change here by Brugge, with Sowah the man coming off and he has been replaced by Maouassa.
Yilmaz is cautioned for an elbow on Jordan.
Batshuayi is booked for pushing Martinez as he went out of play.
Emery makes a late alteration now, bringing Parejo off for Gomez in stoppage time.
A good assist from Dzyuba, who, with his six feet, six inches frame, is always an effective option off the bench.
For an apparent handball, Timber is shown a yellow card by the referee.

RAKITSKIY EQUALISES! 1-1. After Dzyuba missed the earlier penalty, Zenit went for Rakitskiy as the taker. The defender steps up and under immense pressure, drills a low shot into the bottom right corner, beyond Dahlin's despairing dive!
Neymar and Mbappe fly forward for one last attack, but Jesus intervenes by cynically fouling his Brazil international team-mate, and is booked.
Nacho goes into the book for the visitors for catching Sterling in the build-up to a City attack.
Hernandez kicks the ball away and is booked for timewasting.
Malcom is replaced by Krugovoy as Zenit look to secure their point.

GOAAALLLL - CLUB BRUGGE 0-5 RB LEIPZIG - Nkunku scores his second of the night as Leipzig sign off in style. Mignolet did what he could to deny Owusu at the back post, but the ball deflected off his arm towards Nkunku. The Leipzig forward hit his effort on the run, and he found the bottom corner to make it five!
Potential matchwinner Vinicius comes off with only seconds remaining, as Rodrygo makes what he hopes will be a brief cameo.
Reus' flicked header found Malen in acres of space to convert from close range. Dortmund will throw everyone forward now in search of that second goal.
GOAL!!! MALEN PULLS ONE BACK FOR DORTMUND!! Brandt does well on the left and lifts a cross into the middle that Reus nods towards the back post for Malen, who arrives to tap in! It's 3-1 now!
Substitution Daniel Parejo Munoz Manuel Trigueros Munoz
Matic takes his time over the free-kick for United and he's booked for time-wasting.
Substitution Moises Gomez Bordonado Ruben Pena Jimenez
Capaldo is booked for a cynical trip on Djalo.
Woltman enters the action in the closing stages for his Champions League debut to replace Minamino.

GOAL! BOBAN NIKOLOV SAVES IT FOR SHERIFF! 1-1! At the last gasp, the visitors have an equaliser! It's a gut punch for Shakhtar Donetsk and replacement goalkeeper Shevchenko, the finish squeezed under his slow dive, but the close six-yard tap is a powerful one still. The hosts will end their Champions League campaign winless!
Late PSG change now, with Mbappe replaced by Icardi. Surely it is too late to see any more goals?
More cards are flashed, with Camara getting the booking this time for a bad challenge.
Correa replaces Griezmann, who created the Atletico goal with a good cross for Lodi to convert.
Antony notches his second assist of the game. It's a simple one for the winger as he collects in space before rolling a low ball into the six-yard box for Klaassen to convert.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!! KLAASSEN NOTCHES A THIRD FOR AJAX!!! 3-1!!!!! The visitors end the game on the highest of notes as Klaassen converts from close range. Antony continues his dominant performance as he collects in space in the right-inside channel before he cuts the ball back across the face of goal. Klaassen makes a late run and dispatched a close-range finish into the middle of the net.
Those will be the last acts of this match too, as Reinildo is flashed his yellow card.
Emery sends on another defender as Aurier replaces Parejo.
Diaz gets away from Milner and the substitute sticks out a leg to trip the midfielder which earns him a yellow card.
Lille are making a late change here in another attempt to run the clock down. David, who looks to be the match-winner, goes off, with Lihadji on for him.
Reinildo takes a knock in a challenge with Steffen. The referee isn't happy with both of them though and books them, one after the other.
Another late change now and Sancho goes off to a standing ovation from the away fans. Mata is on to see out the last few seconds.
Substitution Ivan Rakitic Karim Rekik
Pjanic lets his frustration show and is booked for a tired foul.
Williams is withdrawn for Bradley, who makes his Champions League bow.
Dentinho goes into the book for Shakhtar after he seemed to sarcastically applaud the referee for a recent decision.
Fourth change for Chelsea now as Loftus-Cheek comes on to replace Mount.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!! WENDEL MAKES IT FOUR!!!! 4-0 ZENIT!!! Wendel wraps up a convincing victory for the hosts with a close-range finish. Azmoun leads a break at the Malmo defence and cuts inside the box from the left flank to shoot on his right foot. Dahlin denies the forward, but Wendel is on the spot to convert the rebound.
Gravenberch has also been booked in the aftermath of his challenge on Yaremchuk.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!! MBAPPPE SCORES AT THE DEATH!!!!!! 1-0 PSG!!!! Mbappe finally gets the breakthrough with a brilliant solo goal. He beats two challenges in the left-inside channel and then places his effort away from Courtois into the bottom-right corner with deadly precision. A huge moment in the tie.
Late change here for Liverpool and Alexander-Arnold goes off to a standing ovation from the home supporters as Phillips replaces him.
Neymar releases the run of Mbappe in the left-inside channel before the forward does the rest with a fine finish.
Having raised his studs in a challenge with Alexander-Arnold, now Gagliardini joins the long list of bookings.
Dortmund played a surprisingly high line as they defended the set-piece, allowing Pjanic to put a quality cross into a dangerous area for Montero to race onto.
Fonte is booked for his late challenge on Lukaku just outside his own penalty area.
After Gravenberch thunders into Yaremchuk with a hefty challenge, Blind complains when the Benfica forward goes down - too heatedly for the referee's liking: that's a yellow card.
Cavani accidentally heads Palomino instead of the ball as he tries to make a clearance and he's booked.
Elia receives a very late booking after catching Albiol in the face as he tried to shield the ball. The Young Boys striker is outraged by the decision.

GOAL!!! BESIKTAS HAVE ONE BACK!!! Pjanic delivers a terrific free-kick into the box and Montero attacks it with conviction, thumping a header beyond Kobel! It's 2-1 now! Can Besiktas find an equaliser?
Okafor follows him with a yellow card of his own for a bad foul on Fernando.
Roca replaces Goretzka for the closing stages of the contest.
AND HE'S MISSED!!! Mbappe looks confident but blazes his penalty high over the bar and Leipzig aren't out of this yet!!
Poulsen is booked in stoppage time for a foul on Marquinhos.
Having hobbled off with some help, Carlos is replaced by Dutch defender Rekik.
But is there a late twist in the game? Ramsey is deemed to have dragged back Krugovoy on the break and Zenit will have a free-kick while the Juve man is booked.
Mahrez is booked for time-wasting at a free-kick.

WHAT A GOOOOOAAAAAALLLLLLL!!!!!! Zenit equalise, again!!!! Dzyuba wins a long ball forward from Douglas and Chelsea don't deal with it, and from the ball back in from Claudinho, Sarr heads away before Ozdoev fires in a firecracker of a volley back towards goal and straight into the top corner!!! What a finish, and we're level again at 3-3!!!!
Taarabt is shown the yellow card for waving at Busquets. Barca take the free-kick but there's no time for them to do anything with it! That's it!

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!! BENZEMA PUTS MADRID AHEAD IN THE TIE!!!!!!!!! 3-1 ON THE NIGHT, 6-5 ON AGGREGATE! Once again in the Champions League Benzema holds his nerve. The Frenchman dispatches his effort low and hard into the bottom-right corner to send the Bernabeu into raptures. What a comeback from the home side.

Red card! Griezmann jinks past Mbemba and it looks - for a moment - as though he'll go through on goal at the death. However, Mbemba cynically trips him over and the referee immediately shows him a straight red card! The defender could have no complaints after preventing such a clear goalscoring chance.
Suarez goes into the book for dissent after not being awarded a free-kick. He continues to talk at the official and needs to be careful.
Xeka is shown a yellow card.
Lingard has two defenders tight to him when he's played in by Ronaldo, and he does brilliantly to deftly touch it to him and duck out of the way of the shot.
Yellow Card Miguel Angelo da Silva Rocha
Bamba tries to break for Lille but ends up catching Onguene instead to give away a free-kick. He won't give the ball back to Salzburg, and he's booked for time-wasting.
Yellow Card Miguel Angelo da Silva Rocha

GOAL! YOUNG BOYS 2-1 MANCHESTER UNITED! United hand Young Boys the victory right at the death! Lingard plays a ill-judged backpass right into the path of Siebatcheu who beats De Gea from the centre of the box! The entire bench is up to celebrate with the American!
Roussillon is booked after bringing down El Haddadi.

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!! WERNER PUTS THE ICING ON THE CAKE!!!! 4-0 CHELSEA!!!!!!! Werner converts a simple chance from six yards to complete the rout for Chelsea. Ziyech robs McKennie of possession down the left flank and he curls a precise low ball across the face of goal. Werner is in the right place at the right time to slot home the strike.
Ziyech capitalises on a mistake from McKennie and supplies a perfect low cross for Werner to score.

RONALDO SCORES! It's a great cross in from Fred on the left which Ronaldo cushions down for Lingard. He does brilliantly to touch it back towards Ronaldo, and he hits it from a very tight angle on the right of the box. Rulli gets a hand to it, but can't stop it from finding the top corner. 2-1 United!
Yellow Card Gonzalo Ariel Montiel
It's very feisty now and Herrera is the latest player to be booked after he tries to block Gulacsi as he went to kick the ball out of his hands.
Ronaldo is booked after taking his shirt off during the goal celebration.
Oliveira gets Porto a consolation goal. 3-1. Oliveira steps up and calmly rolls a neat penalty into the bottom left corner.
Valverde brings down Fernandinho and goes into the book.
Carlos is shown a yellow card.
Yellow Card Mike Maignan
A handball is given against Adeyemi, and he's not happy with the decision. He throws the ball away in frustration and is booked for dissent.
Vinicius raids down the left flank before picking out Benzema to score with an accurate cross.
Mignolet is booked after taking too long over his goal-kick.
Remarkably, Grbic is yet another player to see yellow.
Yellow Card Ivo Grbic

GOALLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLL!!!!! BENZEMA PUTS MADRID BACK IN FRONT IN THE TIE!!!!!!!!!!! 2-3 ON THE NIGHT, 5-4 ON AGGREGATE!!!!! Benzema haunts Chelsea once more by scoring his fourth goal of the tie to put Madrid on course for the semi-finals. Vinicius does well down the left flank and digs out a cross for the Frenchman to attack. He places his effort away from Mendy into the bottom-left corner with precision.
Yellow Card Gonzalo Ariel Montiel
Yellow Card Diego Carlos Santos Silva
Yellow Card Diego Carlos Santos Silva
Yellow Card Ivo Grbic
Montiel is now booked, as the yellow card barely stays in the referee's pocket during the denouement of this match.
Foden fouls De Paul on the charge and goes into the book. Seemingly every player is getting carded at the moment.
Ten Hag makes a last roll of the dice, as Timber comes off and Kudus comes on.

THAT'S TWO! With just seconds on the clock deep into stoppage time, Mir finds himself in acres of space inside the area and latches onto Ocampos' precision ball from the right to prod home the second goal of the game. Three points for Sevilla, they win 2-0!
With plenty of space to pick his pass, Ocampos slots the ball across the area for Mir to secure the win.
Cancelo brings down Carrasco on the edge of the City box on the left flank, handing the home side a free-kick in a dangerous position.

SUAREZ SCORES! From the penalty initially being given to Suarez stepping up to take it, over three minutes had passed, but he didn't let it phase him. He slots it straight down the middle, and it goes through Maignan's legs as the goalkeeper dives to his right. Atletico have turned this around, it's 2-1!
Yellow Card Yusuf Yazici
Yellow Card Yusuf Yazici
In the final seconds, Yazici follows the growing list of men in the referee's fast-filling notebook.
Adan is booked for time-wasting as he dawdles in an attempt to get his team over the line.
Rodri is withdrawn for Sterling for the visitors.
Ziyech replaces Kante with Chelsea in need of a goal to level the tie again.
Sterling brings down Rodrygo on the charge and goes into the book.
Ziyech brings down Vazquez on the charge and goes into the book.
Benzema again has led the line extremely well and is now replaced by Ceballos.
Saul enters the action for the visitors to replace Loftus-Cheek.
Jorginho replaces Kovacic in the middle of the park for the final 15 minutes.
Havertz goes into the book for clipping Alaba in possession.
Azpilicueta is booked without taking the field as he barges over Vazquez in an attempt to get the ball from the sideline.
Zinchenko sticks out a leg to bring down Rodrygo on the charge and goes into the book.
Vinicius takes his time to leave the field much to the frustration of the visitors. Ceballos replaces the Brazilian.
Vallejo enters the action to replace Miltao for the closing stages of the game.
Vazquez enters the action to replace Vinicius as the home side aim to shore up their backline.
Carvajal goes into the book for a loose challenge on Ziyech.
